{"type":"text","timestamp":1782532212107,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"id":"prt_f0732bc540014f9PRSn29Flzhx","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","type":"text","text":"I found the command YAML and prior lineage examples. I’m using them as format references, but I will not invoke the command because its normal write-backs can exceed the requested lineage-only boundary.","time":{"start":1782532193364,"end":1782532212104},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09a137d92d588457016a3f48615cdc819195ecab50dc4cab8f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212161,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jzqbWU62r6gsKjzDh92zxPne","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\n8: \n9: Thin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: > **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n18: \n19: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n20: >\n21: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n22: >\n23: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n24: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n25: > 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n26: >    - `research_topic`\n27: >    - `spec_folder`\n28: >    - `execution_mode`\n29: >    - `maxIterations`\n30: >    - `convergenceThreshold`\n31: > 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n32: >    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n33: >    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n34: > 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n35: >\n36: > This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n37: \n38: ### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n39: \n40: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n41: \n42: ```\n43: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n44: \n45: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n46: │\n47: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n48: │   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-research loop (YAML workflow execution)\n49: │   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n50: │   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n51: │\n52: ├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n53: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n54: │\n55: └─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n56:     │\n57:     ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n58:     │\n59:     ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n60:     │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n61:     │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n62:     │   │                                                            │\n63:     │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n64:     │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n65:     │   │                                                            │\n66:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n67:     │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n68:     │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n69:     │\n70:     └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n71: ```\n72: \n73: **Phase Output:**\n74: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n75: \n76: ### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n77: \n78: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n79: - **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n80: - **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n81: - **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n82:   - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n83: \n84: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n85: \n86: > **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`) and keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n87: \n88: > **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n89: > `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n90: > Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n91: > Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator; the current strict path is designed for fast packet checks and was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n96: \n97: | Purpose | Asset |\n98: |---------|-------|\n99: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n100: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n101: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n102: \n103: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 3. MODE ROUTING\n108: \n109: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n110: 2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n111: 3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n112: 4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n113: 5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n114: 6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n115: 7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n116: 8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n121: \n122: | Mode | Workflow |\n123: |------|----------|\n124: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n125: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n130: \n131: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n132: \n133: - Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n134: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n135: - Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n136: - Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n137: - Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n142: \n143: The selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n144: \n145: For code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the @general verification gate before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-context loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │ \n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","text":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\n> 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n> 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) through the presentation contract and resolve:\n>    - `research_topic`\n>    - `spec_folder`\n>    - `execution_mode`\n>    - `maxIterations`\n>    - `convergenceThreshold`\n> 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\n>    - Auto: `deep_research_auto.yaml`\n>    - Confirm: `deep_research_confirm.yaml`\n> 4. Execute the YAML workflow step by step using those resolved values\n>\n> This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-research loop. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-research loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-research loop and runs  │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:research [arguments]                               │\n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document.\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps.\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML.\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `research_topic`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt in the presentation contract MUST be the first visible response. For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated setup prompt by default; use the auto setup resolution rules in the presentation contract and fail fast when required fields cannot be resolved.\n\n> **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:research:auto`, `/deep:research:confirm`) and keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n\n> **Note:** Late-INIT `spec.md` detection and bounded `spec.md` mutations follow\n> `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`.\n> Acquire `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock` before `folder_state` classification and keep `research/research.md` as the source of truth for any generated findings sync.\n> Targeted strict validation after deep-research spec mutations uses the Node validation orchestrator; the current strict path is designed for fast packet checks and was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached suffixes: `:auto` sets `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS`; `:confirm` sets `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE`; no suffix sets `execution_mode = ASK`.\n2. Treat `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, `--spec-folder`, `--executor`, `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count`, `--executors`, `--concurrency`, and `--no-resource-map` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. For `:auto`, resolve setup from `$ARGUMENTS` flags, any `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, scope-extracted spec-folder paths, and the presentation contract's default resolution table. When all required fields are resolved, persist `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json`, bind runtime YAML placeholders, and load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`.\n4. In `:auto`, ask a targeted Tier-2 question only for `spec_folder` when the topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity; use the named-missing-inputs fail-fast format from the auto-mode contract and do not load YAML.\n5. For `:confirm`, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to bind missing setup values, then load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml`.\n6. For no suffix, use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to choose execution mode and bind missing setup values, then route the resolved interactive choice to the matching YAML.\n7. Lightweight read-only discovery for related spec folders or prior memory may support setup, but it must feed the single consolidated prompt and never split setup questions.\n8. After the selected workflow asset is loaded, execute it step by step using the resolved setup values.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, and reply format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display references.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layout, workflow overview display, convergence-threshold explanation, and user-facing examples.\n- Success and failure result templates, error-handling display, and memory-integration result wording.\n- Next-step suggestions, command-chain wording, skill-reference text, and offline optimization notes.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe selected YAML workflow initializes deep-research state, dispatches fresh `@deep-research` LEAF agents per iteration, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, optionally emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, and refreshes continuity through canonical spec docs. This command does not proceed to implementation.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, route to `/deep:review`. Research path: `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`; review path: `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/research.md","time":{"start":1782532212141,"end":1782532212157}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f4874123481918716517e350e4e80"}},"id":"prt_f0733058a001tw0m98hgLXVt8Z","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212168,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QDBB8gJvF4Hr7Ldp9t7iqCYj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n102:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n103:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n104:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n105:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n106:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n107:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n108:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n109:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n110:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n111:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n112:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n113:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n114:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n115:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n116:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n117:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n118:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n119:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n120: \n121: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n122: # WORKFLOW\n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: workflow:\n125: \n126:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n127:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n128:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n129:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n130:     if_present:\n131:       bind:\n132:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n133:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n134:         artifact_subfolder: null\n135:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n136:     if_absent:\n137:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n138:       outputs:\n139:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n140:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n141:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n142:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n143: \n144:   step_fanout_spawn:\n145:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n146:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n147:     instructions: |\n148:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n149:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n150:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n151:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n152:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n153:     sub_steps:\n154:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n155:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n156:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n157:         command: |\n158:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n159:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n160:             --loop-type research \\\n161:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n162:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n163:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n164:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n165:         wait_for_completion: true\n166:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n167:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n168:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n169:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n170:         dispatch:\n171:           agent: deep-research\n172:           model: opus\n173:           context: |\n174:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n175:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n176:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n177:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n178:               executor: native\n179:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n180:         wait_for_completion: true\n181: \n182:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n183:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n184:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n185:   phase_init:\n186:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n187:     steps:\n188: \n189:       step_preflight_contract:\n190:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n191:         verify:\n192:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n193:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n194:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n195:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n196:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n197: \n198:       step_create_directories:\n199:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n200:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n201: \n202:       step_detect_resource_map:\n203:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n204:         inspect:\n205:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n206:         classify:\n207:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n208:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n209:         outputs:\n210:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n211:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n212: \n213:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n214:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n215:         inspect_legacy:\n216:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n217:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n221:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n222:         on_legacy_read:\n223:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n224: \n225:       step_acquire_lock:\n226:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n227:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n228:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n229:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n230:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n231:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n232:         on_halt:\n233:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n234:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n235:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n236:         on_cancel:\n237:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n238:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n239:         on_workflow_exit:\n240:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n241:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n242: \n243:       step_classify_session:\n244:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n245:         inspect:\n246:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n247:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n248:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n249:         classify:\n250:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n251:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n252:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n253:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n254:         outputs:\n255:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n256:         on_resume:\n257:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n258:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n259:           gate3_classification: write-path\n260:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n261:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n262:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n263:           skip_to: phase_loop\n264:         on_restart:\n265:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n266:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n267:           set:\n268:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n269:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n270:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n271:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n272:           skip_to: step_create_config\n273:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n274:         on_completed_session:\n275:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n276:           halt: true\n277:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n278:         on_invalid_state:\n279:           halt: true\n280:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n281:         on_fresh:\n282:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n283: \n284:       step_create_config:\n285:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n286:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n287:         populate:\n288:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n289:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n290:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n291:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n292:           stuckThreshold: 3\n293:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n294:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n295:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n296:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n297:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n298:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n299:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n300:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n301:           status: \"initialized\"\n302:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n303:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n304:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n305:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n306:           lineage.generation: 1\n307:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n308:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n309: \n310:       step_create_state_log:\n311:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n312:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n313:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n314:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n315:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n316: \n317:       step_create_strategy:\n318:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n319:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n320:         populate:\n321:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n322:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n323:           known_context: \"None\"\n324:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n325:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n326:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n327:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n328: \n329:       step_create_registry:\n330:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n331:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n332:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n333: \n334:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n335:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n336:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n337:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n338:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n339: \n340:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n341:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n342:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n344: \n345:       step_detect_spec_present:\n346:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n347:         inspect:\n348:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n349:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n350:         classify:\n351:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n352:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n353:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n354:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n355:         outputs:\n356:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n357:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n358:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n359: \n360:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n361:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n362:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n363:         branches:\n364:           no-spec:\n365:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n366:             seed_markers:\n367:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n368:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n369:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n370:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n371:             set:\n372:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n373:               validate_spec_doc: true\n374:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n375:           spec-present:\n376:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n377:             set:\n378:               validate_spec_doc: true\n379:             idempotency_check:\n380:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n381:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n382:               if_match:\n383:                 skip_append: true\n384:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n385:               if_no_match:\n386:                 append_only:\n387:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n388:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n389:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n390:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n391:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n393:             verify_markers:\n394:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n395:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n396:             set:\n397:               validate_spec_doc: false\n398:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n399:           conflict-detected:\n400:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n401:             halt: true\n402: \n403:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n404:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n405:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n406:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n407:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n408: \n409:       step_init_complete:\n410:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n411:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n412: \n413:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n414:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n415:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n416:   phase_loop:\n417:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n418:     repeat: true\n419:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n420:     steps:\n421: \n422:       step_read_state:\n423:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n424:         read:\n425:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n426:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n427:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n428:         extract:\n429:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n430:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n431:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n432:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n433:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n434:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n435:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n436:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n437:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n438:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n439:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n440:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n441:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n442:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n443:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n444:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n445:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n446:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n447: \n448:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n449:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n450:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n451:         if_exists:\n452:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n453:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n454:           halt: true\n455:         if_not_exists:\n456:           proceed: true\n457: \n458:       step_graph_convergence:\n459:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n460:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n461:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n462:         outputs:\n463:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n464:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n465:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n466:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n467:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n468:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n469:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n470: \n471:       step_check_convergence:\n472:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n473:         algorithm: |\n474:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n475:           2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n476:           3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n477:           4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n478:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n479:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n480:                signals = []\n481:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n482:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n483:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n484:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n485:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n486:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n487:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n488:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n489:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n490:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n491:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n492:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n493:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n494:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n495:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n496:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n497:                  stop_blocked = true\n498:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n499:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n500:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n501:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n502:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n503:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n504:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n505:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n506:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n507:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n508:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n509:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n510:                  stop_blocked = false\n511:           5. else: CONTINUE\n512:           6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n513:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n514:                if not guardResult.passed:\n515:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n516:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n517:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n518:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n519:         outputs:\n520:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n521:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n522:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n523:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n524:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n525:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n526:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n527:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n528:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n529:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n530:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n531:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n532: \n533:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n534:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n535:         if_blocked:\n536:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n537:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n538:           set:\n539:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n540:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n541:             stop_blocked: false\n542: \n543:       step_handle_convergence:\n544:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n545:         if_stop:\n546:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n547:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n548:         if_stuck_recovery:\n549:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n550:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n551:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n552:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n553:         if_continue:\n554:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n555: \n556:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n557:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n558:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n559:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n560:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n561:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n562:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n563:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n564:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n565: \n566:       step_marker_scan:\n567:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n568:         algorithm: |\n569:           if current_iteration > 1:\n570:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n571:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n572:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n573:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n574:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n575:                 halt with exit code 2\n576:         note: |\n577:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n578:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n579:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n580:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n581: \n582:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n583:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n584:         resolve_executor:\n585:           source: \"config.executor\"\n586:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n587:         pre_dispatch:\n588:           generate_summary: |\n589:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n590:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n591:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n592:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n593:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n594:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n595:           render_prompt_pack:\n596:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n597:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n598:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n599:             variables:\n600:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n601:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n602:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n603:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n604:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n605:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n606:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n607:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n608:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n609:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n610:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n611:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n612:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n613:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n614:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n615:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n616:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n617:           args:\n618:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n619:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n620:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n621:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n622:         if_native:\n623:           dispatch:\n624:             agent: deep-research\n625:             model: opus\n626:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n627:           wait_for_completion: true\n628:         if_cli_codex:\n629:           command: |\n630:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n631:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n632: \n633:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n634:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n635: \n636:             const executor = {\n637:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n638:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n639:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n640:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n641:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n642:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n643:             };\n644: \n645:             process.exit(\n646:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n647:                 command: 'codex',\n648:                 args: [\n649:                   'exec',\n650:                   '--model',\n651:                   executor.model,\n652:                   '-c',\n653:                   `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n654:                   '-c',\n655:                   `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n656:                   '-c',\n657:                   'approval_policy=never',\n658:                   '--sandbox',\n659:                   resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n660:                   '-',\n661:                 ],\n662:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n663:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n664:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n665:                 executor,\n666:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n667:                 input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n668:               }),\n669:             );\n670:             EOF\n671:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n672:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n673:           wait_for_completion: true\n674:         if_cli_claude_code:\n675:           command: |\n676:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n677:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n678: \n679:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n680:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n681: \n682:             const executor = {\n683:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n684:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n685:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n686:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n687:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n688:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n689:             };\n690:             const args = [\n691:               '-p',\n692:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n693:               '--model',\n694:               executor.model,\n695:               '--permission-mode',\n696:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n697:               '--output-format',\n698:               'text',\n699:             ];\n700:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n701:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n702:             }\n703: \n704:             process.exit(\n705:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n706:                 command: 'claude',\n707:                 args,\n708:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n709:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n710:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n711:                 executor,\n712:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n713:               }),\n714:             );\n715:             EOF\n716:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n717:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n718:           wait_for_completion: true\n719:           notes:\n720:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n721:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n722:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n723:         record_executor_audit:\n724:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n725:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n726:           field: \"executor\"\n727:           value:\n728:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n729:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n730:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n731:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n732:         if_cli_opencode:\n733:           command: |\n734:             opencode run \\\n735:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n736:               --format json \\\n737:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n738:               --pure \\\n739:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n740:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n741:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n742:               </dev/null\n743:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n744:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n745:           wait_for_completion: true\n746:           render_hint:\n747:             optional_variant_flag: |\n748:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n749:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n750:           notes:\n751:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n752:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n753:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n754:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-754. Use offset=755 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          5. else: CONTINUE\n          6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args: [\n                  'exec',\n                  '--model',\n                  executor.model,\n                  '-c',\n                  `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  'approval_policy=never',\n                  '--sandbox',\n                  resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                  '-',\n                ],\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":754,"totalLines":755,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782532212154,"end":1782532212164}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f487412448191b39814eaff08c901"}},"id":"prt_f073305b70017uEM5PpTrbioHr","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212175,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ifU2cij6VqlCnOrJnHwoZenn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"research loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n9:   - \"research pause sentinel\"\n10:   - \"research synthesis phase\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\n17: \n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n35: \n36: ### Phase Model\n37: \n38: The deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n39: \n40: Runtime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n41: - Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n42: - Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n46: │  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n47: │          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n48: │ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n49: │ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n50: │ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n51: │          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n52: │          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n53: │          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n54: │          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n55: └──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n61: \n62: ### Purpose\n63: Set up all state files for a new research session.\n64: \n65: ### Steps\n66: \n67: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n68:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n69:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n70:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n71:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n72: 2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n73:    - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n74:    - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n75:    - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n76: 3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n77: 4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n78: 5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n79: 6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n80:    - Topic from user input\n81:    - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n82:    - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n83:    - Research boundaries from config\n84: 6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n85:    - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n86:    - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n87:    - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n88:    - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n89:    - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n90:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n91: 7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n92: 7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n93:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n94:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n95:    - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n96:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n97:    - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n98: 8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n99: \n100: ### Outputs\n101: - `research/deep-research-config.json`\n102: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n103: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n104: \n105: ### Auto-Resume Protocol\n106: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n107: 1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n108: 2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n109: 3. Read strategy.md for current state\n110: 4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n111: 5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n112: \n113: ```json\n114: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n115: ```\n116: \n117: 6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n118: \n119: ### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n120: \n121: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n122: \n123: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n124: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n125: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n126: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n127: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n128: \n129: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n130: \n131: ```json\n132: {\n133:   \"type\": \"event\",\n134:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n135:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n136:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n137:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n138:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n139:   \"generation\": <number>,\n140:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n141:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n142:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n151: \n152: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n153: \n154: #### Step 1: Read State\n155: - Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n156: - Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n157: \n158: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n159: Run the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n160: - Max iterations reached? STOP\n161: - Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n162: - Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n163: - All questions answered? STOP\n164: - Otherwise: CONTINUE\n165: \n166: #### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n167: \n168: When the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n169: 1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n170: 2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n171: 3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n172: 4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n173:    - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n174:    - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n175:    - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n176: 5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n177: 6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n178: \n179: If the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n180: \n181: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n182: \n183: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n184: \n185: 1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n186: 2. If present:\n187:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n188:    - Halt the loop with message:\n189:      ```text\n190:      Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n191:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n192:      ```\n193:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n194: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n195:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n196:    - Continue from step_read_state\n197: \n198: Pause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n199: \n200: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n201: \n202: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n203: \n204: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n205: \n206: ```text\n207: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n208: Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\n209: Questions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n210: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n211: Recovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\n212: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n213: ```\n214: \n215: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n216: \n217: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n218: Dispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n219: ```text\n220: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n221: \n222: Research Topic: {config.topic}\n223: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n224: Focus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\n225: Remaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\n226: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\n227: Resource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\n228: State Files:\n229:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n230:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n231:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\n232: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n233: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n234: ```\n235: \n236: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n237: \n238: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n239: \n240: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n241: - `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n242: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n243: \n244: All branches share:\n245: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n246: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n247: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n248: \n249: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n250: \n251: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n252: \n253: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n254: \n255: The dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n256: \n257: #### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n258: \n259: After dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n260: - **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n261: - **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n262: - If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n263:   1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n264:   2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n265:   3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n266: - Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n267: \n268: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n269: After agent completes:\n270: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n271: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n272: 3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n273:    - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n274:    - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n275: 4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n276: 5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n277: 6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n278: 7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n279: \n280: #### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n281: \n282: After evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n283: \n284: 1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n285: 2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n286:    - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n287:    - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n288:    - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n289:    - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n290:    - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n291:    - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n292: 3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n293: 4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n294: 5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n295: 6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n296: \n297: In **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n298: \n299: #### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n300: \n301: This checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n302: \n303: After each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n304: \n305: 1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n306:    ```bash\n307:    git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n308:    git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n309:    git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n310:    git add research/findings-registry.json\n311:    git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n312:    git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n313:    ```\n314: 2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n315: 3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n316: 4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n317: \n318: Checkpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n319: \n320: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n321: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n322: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n323: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n324: \n325: ### Ideas Backlog Convention\n326: \n327: A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n328: \n329: #### Check Points\n330: \n331: The orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n332: \n333: 1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n334: 2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n335: 3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n336: \n337: #### Format\n338: \n339: ```markdown\n340: Title: Research Ideas\n341: \n342: Section: Deferred (not yet explored)\n343: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n344: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n345: \n346: Section: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n347: - [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n348: ```\n349: \n350: Users can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n351: \n352: ### Stuck Recovery Protocol\n353: When stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n354: \n355: **Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\n356: Before selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n357: 1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n358: 2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n359:    - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n360:    - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n361:    - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n362:    - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n363:    - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n364: 3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n365: 4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n366: \n367: **Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n368: 1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n369: 2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n370: 3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n371: 4. Reset stuck counter\n372: 5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n373: \n374: ### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n375: \n376: When agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n377: \n378: 1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n379: 2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n380: 3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n381:    - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n382:    - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n383:    - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n384:    - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n385:    - Update strategy.md\n386:    - Append iteration record to JSONL\n387: 4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n388: 5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n389: \n390: **Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n395: \n396: An optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n397: \n398: ### When to Use Waves\n399: \n400: - 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n401: - Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n402: - Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n403: \n404: ### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n405: \n406: ```text\n407: Wave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n408:   |\n409:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n410:   +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n411:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n412:   |\n413: Scoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n414:   |\n415: Wave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n416:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n417:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n418:   |\n419: Repeat until convergence\n420: ```\n421: \n422: ### Scoring and Pruning\n423: \n424: In a future wave-enabled runtime:\n425: 1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n426: 2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n427: 3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n428: 4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n429: 5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n430: \n431: ### Breakthrough Detection\n432: \n433: When any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n434: \n435: 1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n436: 2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n437: 3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n438: 4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n439: \n440: ### Wave JSONL Records\n441: \n442: Wave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n443: \n444: ### Integration with Sequential Loop\n445: \n446: - Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n447: - The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n448: - A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n449: - The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n454: \n455: An alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n456: \n457: ### Motivation\n458: \n459: The standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n460: \n461: ### Dispatch Mechanism\n462: \n463: Replace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n464: \n465: 1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n466:    - Strategy.md (current state)\n467:    - Config.json (parameters)\n468:    - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n469:    - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n470:    - Full agent protocol instructions\n471: 2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n472: 3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n473: 4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n474: 5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n475: 6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n476: \n477: ### Trade-offs\n478: \n479: | Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n480: |--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n481: | Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n482: | Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n483: | Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n484: | Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n485: | Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n486: \n487: ### When to Use\n488: \n489: - Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n490: - Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n491: - Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n492: \n493: **Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n494: \n495: ---\n496: \n497: ## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n498: \n499: ### Purpose\n500: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n501: \n502: ### Steps\n503: \n504: 1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n505: 2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n506: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n507:    - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n508:    - Organize by section topic\n509:    - Add citations from iteration files\n510:    - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n511:    - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n512:    - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n513:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n514:      - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n515:      - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n516:      - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n517:      - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n518:      - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n519:      - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n520: 4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n521: 5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n522: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n523: \n524: ### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n525: - If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n526: - If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n531: \n532: ### Purpose\n533: Preserve research context to memory system.\n534: \n535: ### Steps\n536: \n537: 1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n538: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n539: 3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n540: \n541: ---\n542: \n543: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n544: \n545: ```text\n546: [INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n547:     |\n548: [ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n549:     |\n550: [EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n551:     |\n552:     |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n553:     |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n554:     |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n555: \n556: [STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n557:     |\n558:     |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n559:     |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n560: \n561: [SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n562:     |\n563: [SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n564:     |\n565: [COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n566: ```\n567: \n568: Hook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n573: \n574: | Error | Phase | Action |\n575: |-------|-------|--------|\n576: | Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n577: | WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n578: | State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n579: | JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n580: | 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n581: | Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n582: | Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n583: \n584: ### State Recovery Protocol\n585: \n586: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n587: \n588: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n589: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n590: | 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n591: | 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n592: | 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n593: | 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n594: | 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n595: \n596: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n601: \n602: In confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n603: \n604: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n605: |---------------|----------|\n606: | After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n607: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n608: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n609: | After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n610: \n611: ---\n612: \n613: ## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n614: \n615: Deep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n616: \n617: This reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.\n\n(End of file - total 617 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n### Phase Model\n\nThe deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n\nRuntime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n- Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n```text\n┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n│          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n│ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n│ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n│ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n│          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n└──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\nSet up all state files for a new research session.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n   - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n   - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n   - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n   - Topic from user input\n   - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n   - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n   - Research boundaries from config\n6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n   - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n   - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n   - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n   - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n   - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n\n### Outputs\n- `research/deep-research-config.json`\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n\n### Auto-Resume Protocol\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n3. Read strategy.md for current state\n4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n```\n\n6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n\n### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n- Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n- Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\nRun the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n- Max iterations reached? STOP\n- Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n- Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n- All questions answered? STOP\n- Otherwise: CONTINUE\n\n#### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n\nWhen the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n   - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n   - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n\nIf the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```text\n     Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\nPause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```text\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\nSegment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\nQuestions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nRecovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\nResource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\nThe dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n\n#### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n\nAfter dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n- **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n- **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n\nAfter evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n\n1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n   - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n   - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n   - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n   - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n   - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n   - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n\nIn **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n\n#### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nThis checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n\nAfter each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n\n1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n   ```bash\n   git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n   git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n   git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n   git add research/findings-registry.json\n   git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n   git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n   ```\n2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n\nCheckpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Ideas Backlog Convention\n\nA persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n\n#### Check Points\n\nThe orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n\n1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n\n#### Format\n\n```markdown\nTitle: Research Ideas\n\nSection: Deferred (not yet explored)\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n\nSection: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n- [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n```\n\nUsers can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n\n### Stuck Recovery Protocol\nWhen stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n\n**Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\nBefore selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n   - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n   - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n   - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n   - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n   - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n\n**Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n4. Reset stuck counter\n5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n\n### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nWhen agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n\n1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n   - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n   - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n   - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n   - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - Update strategy.md\n   - Append iteration record to JSONL\n4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n\n**Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n\n### When to Use Waves\n\n- 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n- Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n- Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n\n### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n\n```text\nWave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n  |\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n  +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n  |\nScoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n  |\nWave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n  |\nRepeat until convergence\n```\n\n### Scoring and Pruning\n\nIn a future wave-enabled runtime:\n1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n\n### Breakthrough Detection\n\nWhen any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n\n1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n\n### Wave JSONL Records\n\nWave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n\n### Integration with Sequential Loop\n\n- Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n- The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n- A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n- The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n\n### Dispatch Mechanism\n\nReplace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n\n1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n   - Strategy.md (current state)\n   - Config.json (parameters)\n   - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n   - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n   - Full agent protocol instructions\n2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n| Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n| Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n| Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n| Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n- Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n   - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n   - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n   - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n     - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n     - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n     - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n     - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n     - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n     - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\nPreserve research context to memory system.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n```text\n[INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n    |\n[ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n    |\n[EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n    |\n    |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n    |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n\n[STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n    |\n    |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n\n[SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n    |\n[SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n    |\n[COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n```\n\nHook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n\n---\n\n## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Error | Phase | Action |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n| WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n| State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n| JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n| Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n\n### State Recovery Protocol\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n| 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n| 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n| 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n\nIn confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n\nDeep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n\nThis reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":617,"totalLines":617,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1782532212160,"end":1782532212174}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f4874124c8191abaa3a20d5faea81"}},"id":"prt_f073305bb001s3fM9UENqYCTnU","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212202,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WwbHbqrNC5apLCFzo5Xhlfyi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: State Format Reference\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state format\"\n6:   - \"research state packet hub\"\n7:   - \"research file ownership model\"\n8:   - \"research file protection rules\"\n9:   - \"research packet location\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # State Format Reference\n16: \n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n30: \n31: ### Routed Details\n32: \n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n36: \n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n38: \n39: ### Packet Summary\n40: \n41: The deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n42: \n43: | File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n44: |------|--------|---------|------------|\n45: | `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n46: | `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n47: | `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n48: | `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n49: | `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n50: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n51: | `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n52: | `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n53: | `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n54: \n55: The artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n60: \n61: Root specs use:\n62: \n63: ```text\n64: {spec_folder}/research/\n65: ```\n66: \n67: Child-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n68: \n69: - first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n70: - a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n71: - continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n72: \n73: This avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n78: \n79: | Owner | Writes |\n80: |-------|--------|\n81: | Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n82: | Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n83: | Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n84: | Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n85: \n86: The reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n91: \n92: | Protection | Meaning |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n95: | `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n96: | `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n97: | `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n98: | `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n99: \n100: The config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n105: \n106: | Resource | Use When |\n107: |----------|----------|\n108: | `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n109: | `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n110: | `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n111: | `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n112: | `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n117: \n118: - Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n119: - Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n120: - Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n\n### Routed Details\n\n- `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n- `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n- `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n\nFor iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n\n### Packet Summary\n\nThe deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n\n| File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n|------|--------|---------|------------|\n| `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n| `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n| `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n| `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n| `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n| `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n| `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n| `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n\nThe artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n\nRoot specs use:\n\n```text\n{spec_folder}/research/\n```\n\nChild-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n\n- first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n- a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n- continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n\nThis avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n\n| Owner | Writes |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n| Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n| Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n| Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n\nThe reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n\n| Protection | Meaning |\n|------------|---------|\n| `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n| `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n| `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n| `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n| `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n\nThe config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n| `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n| `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n| `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n| `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n- Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n- Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":120,"totalLines":120,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1782532212177,"end":1782532212197}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f4874125481919d0249ec754e9588"}},"id":"prt_f073305c700155umHC8mBgl26o","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212202,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aURvXMNSHA5pA6QefsSWvtHx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1782532212182,"end":1782532212200}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f4874125c8191872078d16813e4fc"}},"id":"prt_f073305d4001IOB3cKfJ7MaqGg","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212210,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_18r3MxuWIEsvdihmRg4BYxRy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n58: \n59: ### stopReason Values\n60: \n61: | Value | When It Is Used |\n62: |-------|-----------------|\n63: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n64: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n65: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n66: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n67: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n68: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n69: \n70: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n71: \n72: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n73: \n74: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n75: |------------------------|------------------|\n76: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n77: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n78: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n79: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n80: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n81: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n82: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n87: \n88: ### Decision Order\n89: \n90: ```text\n91: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n92: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n93: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n94: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n95: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n96: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n97: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n98: 8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Composite Signal Weights\n102: \n103: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n104: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n105: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n106: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n107: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n108: \n109: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n114: \n115: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n116: \n117: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n118: |------|------|---------|\n119: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n120: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n121: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n122: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n123: \n124: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n129: \n130: | Resource | Use When |\n131: |----------|----------|\n132: | `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n133: | `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n134: | `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n135: | `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n136: | `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n137: | `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n142: \n143: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n144: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n145: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1782532212188,"end":1782532212209}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f4874126481918456fad1612e106c"}},"id":"prt_f073305d8001wOaUZu04MRp45B","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532212212,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aISZ6vUjLozLymQN7SXSRt6G","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md","offset":1,"limit":800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\"\n3: description: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out research config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge → canonical research.md.\"\n4: version: 1.14.0.3\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # DR-052 -- Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\n8: \n9: This document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DR-052`.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n14: \n15: End-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the research loop.\n16: \n17: ### Why This Matters\n18: \n19: The CLI fan-out path is the primary production scenario. If `step_fanout_spawn` is absent\n20: or the `--executor` flag parsing produces `config.executor` instead of `config.fanout` when\n21: two executors are specified, no fan-out dispatch happens silently.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n26: \n27: - Objective: Confirm the research YAML dispatches CLI lineages via `fanout-run.cjs` when two executor flags are present, that both lineages are isolated, and that the merged registry feeds `step_compile_research`.\n28: - Real user request: `/deep:research:auto \"test topic\" --executor=cli-codex --model=o4-mini --label=codex --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude --concurrency=2`\n29: - Expected execution process: 1. Setup binds two executors → `config.fanout` (not `config.executor`). 2. `step_resolve_artifact_root` resolves base `artifact_dir`. 3. `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs` with both CLI lineages. 4. Pool spawns two subprocesses in parallel. 5. Each writes to `lineages/codex/` and `lineages/claude/`. 6. `step_fanout_merge` reads both lineage registries, deduplicates. 7. `step_compile_research` emits canonical `research.md`.\n30: - Expected signals: `step_fanout_spawn` present in YAML with `skip_when`; `step_fanout_merge` present in `phase_synthesis` with `skip_when`; `--executor` docs list 2+ → `config.fanout` default policy; `fanout-run.vitest.ts` confirms pool isolation.\n31: - Pass/fail: PASS if source inspection confirms the full dispatch chain and unit tests agree; FAIL if any step is missing, `skip_when` guard absent, or docs lack the fan-out default policy.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n36: \n37: ### Prerequisites\n38: \n39: - Working directory is repository root.\n40: - `deep_research_auto.yaml` and `research.md` present.\n41: - `fanout-run.cjs` and `fanout-merge.cjs` present.\n42: \n43: ### Steps\n44: \n45: 1. `bash: grep -n \"step_fanout_spawn\\|step_fanout_merge\\|fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\\|skip_when\" .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml | head -20`\n46: 2. Confirm `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs --loop-type research`.\n47: 3. Confirm `step_fanout_merge` calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type research` and has `skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"`.\n48: 4. `bash: grep -n \"fanout_executors\\|--executor\\|--executors\\|--concurrency\\|config.fanout\\|config.executor\" .opencode/commands/deep/research.md | head -20`\n49: 5. Confirm default policy: 2+ `--executor` → `config.fanout`.\n50: 6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n51: 7. Confirm 5/5 pass (pool dispatch + lineage isolation confirmed by unit tests).\n52: \n53: ### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n54: \n55: 1. Check user-facing command docs before YAML internals.\n56: 2. Verify the `skip_when` guard before checking the command body.\n57: 3. Cross-reference `fanout-run.cjs` and `fanout-merge.cjs` paths match what the YAML calls.\n58: 4. Anchor the verdict on captured `grep` output and vitest results.\n59: \n60: ### Expected Outcome\n61: \n62: Source inspection confirms dispatch chain. Unit tests confirm pool isolation and lineage dir creation.\n63: \n64: ### Failure Modes\n65: \n66: - `step_fanout_spawn` absent from YAML: fan-out never triggers regardless of config.\n67: - `skip_when` guard missing: fan-out step runs in single-executor mode, calling `fanout-run.cjs` with absent config.\n68: - Default policy missing from docs: operators cannot understand when `config.fanout` vs `config.executor` is written.\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. SOURCE FILES\n73: \n74: ### Implementation\n75: \n76: | File | Role |\n77: |---|---|\n78: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge`, `step_resolve_artifact_root` |\n79: | `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md` | `--executor` flag docs, default policy, fan-out examples |\n80: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Pool driver for CLI lineages |\n81: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Research dedup merge |\n82: \n83: ### Validation\n84: \n85: | File | Role |\n86: |---|---|\n87: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | CLI lineage spawn + isolation |\n88: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | Research registry dedup |\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n93: \n94: - Group: Fan-Out\n95: - Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`\n96: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md`\n97: - Expected verdict mode: GREEN when source inspection + unit tests agree\n98: - Wall-time estimate: 10-20 min\n\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\"\ndescription: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out research config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge → canonical research.md.\"\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# DR-052 -- Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DR-052`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nEnd-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the research loop.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThe CLI fan-out path is the primary production scenario. If `step_fanout_spawn` is absent\nor the `--executor` flag parsing produces `config.executor` instead of `config.fanout` when","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\"\ndescription: \"Validate that a two-CLI-lineage fan-out research config triggers step_fanout_spawn → fanout-run.cjs pool → two isolated lineages sub-packets → step_fanout_merge → canonical research.md.\"\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# DR-052 -- Fan-out research with two CLI lineages\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DR-052`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nEnd-to-end structural validation of the CLI fan-out path in the research loop.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThe CLI fan-out path is the primary production scenario. If `step_fanout_spawn` is absent\nor the `--executor` flag parsing produces `config.executor` instead of `config.fanout` when\ntwo executors are specified, no fan-out dispatch happens silently.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Objective: Confirm the research YAML dispatches CLI lineages via `fanout-run.cjs` when two executor flags are present, that both lineages are isolated, and that the merged registry feeds `step_compile_research`.\n- Real user request: `/deep:research:auto \"test topic\" --executor=cli-codex --model=o4-mini --label=codex --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude --concurrency=2`\n- Expected execution process: 1. Setup binds two executors → `config.fanout` (not `config.executor`). 2. `step_resolve_artifact_root` resolves base `artifact_dir`. 3. `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs` with both CLI lineages. 4. Pool spawns two subprocesses in parallel. 5. Each writes to `lineages/codex/` and `lineages/claude/`. 6. `step_fanout_merge` reads both lineage registries, deduplicates. 7. `step_compile_research` emits canonical `research.md`.\n- Expected signals: `step_fanout_spawn` present in YAML with `skip_when`; `step_fanout_merge` present in `phase_synthesis` with `skip_when`; `--executor` docs list 2+ → `config.fanout` default policy; `fanout-run.vitest.ts` confirms pool isolation.\n- Pass/fail: PASS if source inspection confirms the full dispatch chain and unit tests agree; FAIL if any step is missing, `skip_when` guard absent, or docs lack the fan-out default policy.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Working directory is repository root.\n- `deep_research_auto.yaml` and `research.md` present.\n- `fanout-run.cjs` and `fanout-merge.cjs` present.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. `bash: grep -n \"step_fanout_spawn\\|step_fanout_merge\\|fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\\|skip_when\" .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml | head -20`\n2. Confirm `step_fanout_spawn_cli` calls `fanout-run.cjs --loop-type research`.\n3. Confirm `step_fanout_merge` calls `fanout-merge.cjs --loop-type research` and has `skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"`.\n4. `bash: grep -n \"fanout_executors\\|--executor\\|--executors\\|--concurrency\\|config.fanout\\|config.executor\" .opencode/commands/deep/research.md | head -20`\n5. Confirm default policy: 2+ `--executor` → `config.fanout`.\n6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n7. Confirm 5/5 pass (pool dispatch + lineage isolation confirmed by unit tests).\n\n### RECOMMENDED ORCHESTRATION PROCESS\n\n1. Check user-facing command docs before YAML internals.\n2. Verify the `skip_when` guard before checking the command body.\n3. Cross-reference `fanout-run.cjs` and `fanout-merge.cjs` paths match what the YAML calls.\n4. Anchor the verdict on captured `grep` output and vitest results.\n\n### Expected Outcome\n\nSource inspection confirms dispatch chain. Unit tests confirm pool isolation and lineage dir creation.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- `step_fanout_spawn` absent from YAML: fan-out never triggers regardless of config.\n- `skip_when` guard missing: fan-out step runs in single-executor mode, calling `fanout-run.cjs` with absent config.\n- Default policy missing from docs: operators cannot understand when `config.fanout` vs `config.executor` is written.\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | `step_fanout_spawn`, `step_fanout_merge`, `step_resolve_artifact_root` |\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md` | `--executor` flag docs, default policy, fan-out examples |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Pool driver for CLI lineages |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | Research dedup merge |\n\n### Validation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | CLI lineage spawn + isolation |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts` | Research registry dedup |\n\n---\n\n## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n\n- Group: Fan-Out\n- Canonical root source: `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`\n- Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md`\n- Expected verdict mode: GREEN when source inspection + unit tests agree\n- Wall-time estimate: 10-20 min","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":98,"totalLines":98,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/08--fanout/fanout-cli-lineages-research.md","time":{"start":1782532212193,"end":1782532212211}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a137d92d588457016a3f487412688191b2aa7a02939d1548"}},"id":"prt_f073305dd001KXibKIAzc6K0C7","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f0732a610001Eq41VJSTiDBEYp"}}
