ons: 0\n30: - resolvedQuestions: 5\n31: \n32: ## 3. Questions\n33: \n34: - Answered: 5/5\n35: - [x] Q1: Competitor capabilities surveyed.\n36: - [x] Q2: Net-new vs packet 005 deduped.\n37: - [x] Q3: ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts recorded per skill.\n38: - [x] Q4: Out-of-scope features captured as negative knowledge.\n39: - [x] Q5: Prioritized recommendation set produced.\n40: \n41: ## 4. Trend\n42: \n43: - Last 3 ratios: 0.72 -> 0.58 -> 0.31 (declining)\n44: - Stuck count: 0\n45: - Guard violations: none\n46: - Convergence score: 0.69\n47: - Source diversity: primary docs for 4 required tools plus local skill and prior-research files\n48: \n49: ## 5. Dead Ends\n50: \n51: - Hosted deployment/backend agent: platform scope, not local CLI-skill scope.\n52: - Preset palette/font/layout chooser: conflicts with anti-default design judgment.\n53: - MagicPath-owned git/PR workflow: belongs to sk-git/system workflows.\n54: - Automated subtle visual diff: browser testing is useful but documented as weak for subtle design details.\n55: - Two-way generated component source ownership: use generated source plus wrapper boundary.\n56: \n57: ## 6. Next Focus\n58: \n59: Lineage complete. Merge host should reconcile this synthesis with the sibling lineage when available.\n60: \n61: ## 7. Active Risks\n62: \n63: - Sibling `opus48-claude2` had no completed iteration artifacts available to this lineage at synthesis time, so cross-lineage reconciliation remains a host merge task.\n64: - Some adjacent-product pages were broad; core recommendations rely on primary docs for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe.\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55fast lineage\n\nAuto-generated summary from lineage JSONL, registry, and strategy state.\n\n## 1. Status\n\n- Topic: Adoptable ideas from competitor AI design tools for sk-design-interface and mcp-magicpath\n- Started: 2026-06-14T09:20:00Z\n- Status: COMPLETE\n- Iterations: 5 of 5\n- Stop reason: maxIterationsReached\n- Session ID: fanout-gpt55fast-1781420686076-jgor8g\n- Lifecycle mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n- Write boundary: artifact directory only; parent spec write-back skipped by operator constraint\n\n## 2. Progress\n\n| # | Focus | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|----------|--------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55fast lineage\n\nAuto-generated summary from lineage JSONL, registry, and strategy state.\n\n## 1. Status\n\n- Topic: Adoptable ideas from competitor AI design tools for sk-design-interface and mcp-magicpath\n- Started: 2026-06-14T09:20:00Z\n- Status: COMPLETE\n- Iterations: 5 of 5\n- Stop reason: maxIterationsReached\n- Session ID: fanout-gpt55fast-1781420686076-jgor8g\n- Lifecycle mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n- Write boundary: artifact directory only; parent spec write-back skipped by operator constraint\n\n## 2. Progress\n\n| # | Focus | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | v0 live visual editing, registries, Figma import | 1.00 | 6 | complete |\n| 2 | Lovable design guidance, preview toolbar, adherence, browser testing | 0.82 | 7 | complete |\n| 3 | Figma Make plan mode, Make kits, guidelines, local codebase | 0.72 | 7 | complete |\n| 4 | Subframe deterministic code, sync boundaries, MCP access | 0.58 | 6 | complete |\n| 5 | Deduplication and prioritized adoption matrix | 0.31 | 8 | complete |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: 5\n- keyFindings: 8\n- openQuestions: 0\n- resolvedQuestions: 5\n\n## 3. Questions\n\n- Answered: 5/5\n- [x] Q1: Competitor capabilities surveyed.\n- [x] Q2: Net-new vs packet 005 deduped.\n- [x] Q3: ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts recorded per skill.\n- [x] Q4: Out-of-scope features captured as negative knowledge.\n- [x] Q5: Prioritized recommendation set produced.\n\n## 4. Trend\n\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.72 -> 0.58 -> 0.31 (declining)\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none\n- Convergence score: 0.69\n- Source diversity: primary docs for 4 required tools plus local skill and prior-research files\n\n## 5. Dead Ends\n\n- Hosted deployment/backend agent: platform scope, not local CLI-skill scope.\n- Preset palette/font/layout chooser: conflicts with anti-default design judgment.\n- MagicPath-owned git/PR workflow: belongs to sk-git/system workflows.\n- Automated subtle visual diff: browser testing is useful but documented as weak for subtle design details.\n- Two-way generated component source ownership: use generated source plus wrapper boundary.\n\n## 6. Next Focus\n\nLineage complete. Merge host should reconcile this synthesis with the sibling lineage when available.\n\n## 7. Active Risks\n\n- Sibling `opus48-claude2` had no completed iteration artifacts available to this lineage at synthesis time, so cross-lineage reconciliation remains a host merge task.\n- Some adjacent-product pages were broad; core recommendations rely on primary docs for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":64,"totalLines":64,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1782532788592,"end":1782532788596}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db3c8b307f56147016a3f4ab472808191992e0394f369b728"}},"id":"prt_f073bd14d0015BmfZqQM3S4hLn","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f073b88ca0015DUh7WpkP1fCum"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532788635,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_X8XTcRsa7kmEVov8PBb2lSxI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n3:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n4:     {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"summary\":\"Distinctive capabilities surveyed across v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-001\",\"iteration-002\",\"iteration-003\",\"iteration-004\"]},\n5:     {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"summary\":\"Deduped against packet 005; net-new patterns isolated from Claude Design parity overlap.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-005\"]},\n6:     {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"summary\":\"ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts recorded per local skill.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#7-ranked-net-new-ideas\"]},\n7:     {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"summary\":\"Negative knowledge captured for hosted, platform, preset, and over-automation directions.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#10-eliminated-alternatives\"]},\n8:     {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"summary\":\"Prioritized recommendation set produced for merge host.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#11-recommendations\"]}\n9:   ],\n10:   \"keyFindings\": [\n11:     {\"id\":\"F1\",\"title\":\"Pre-build direction gate\",\"summary\":\"Lovable and Subframe generate multiple visual directions before committing to a build; adapt as a brief-specific critique gate, not presets.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md\"]},\n12:     {\"id\":\"F2\",\"title\":\"Element-target feedback grammar\",\"summary\":\"v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe all let users point to/select/annotate a rendered element, then describe a scoped change.\",\"sources\":[\"https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md\"]},\n13:     {\"id\":\"F3\",\"title\":\"Design-system adherence scanner\",\"summary\":\"Lovable explicitly checks for raw colors, one-off values, inline overrides, and local component misuse; Figma Make guidelines document token pitfalls and don't-do rules.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits\"]},\n14:     {\"id\":\"F4\",\"title\":\"Editable plan artifact before build\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make plan mode creates a reviewable plan markdown file before code changes; local skills can borrow the small artifact pattern for complex design work.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make\"]},\n15:     {\"id\":\"F5\",\"title\":\"Presentational/generated boundary\",\"summary\":\"Subframe separates deterministic presentational code from wrapper-owned business logic; mcp-magicpath should make the same boundary explicit for installed/generated components.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md\"]},\n16:     {\"id\":\"F6\",\"title\":\"Guidelines as design-system context\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make kits and Lovable design systems put machine-readable rules near component/tokens; local skills can emit and consume compact guidelines without hosting a platform.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\"]},\n17:     {\"id\":\"F7\",\"title\":\"Fidelity loop limitations\",\"summary\":\"Browser testing is useful for behavior and screenshots but not subtle color/detail judgment; completion gates should state this limitation.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md\"]},\n18:     {\"id\":\"F8\",\"title\":\"MCP/design-document access\",\"summary\":\"Subframe exposes pages, components, theme, and design documents through MCP; MagicPath remains CLI-only, so adopt the output-manifest idea rather than the server surface.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md\"]}\n19:   ],\n20:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n21:     {\"approach\":\"Hosted deployment/backend agent\",\"reason\":\"Platform scope; not local skill scope.\",\"evidence\":\"https://vercel.com/docs/v0\"},\n22:     {\"approach\":\"Preset palette/font/layout chooser\",\"reason\":\"Conflicts with anti-default design judgment.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md\"},\n23:     {\"approach\":\"MagicPath-owned git branch/PR management\",\"reason\":\"Belongs to sk-git, not mcp-magicpath.\",\"evidence\":\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase\"},\n24:     {\"approach\":\"Automated subtle visual diff as sole quality gate\",\"reason\":\"Browser testing is documented as unreliable for subtle design details.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md\"},\n25:     {\"approach\":\"Two-way generated component source ownership\",\"reason\":\"Use generated source plus wrapper boundary; do not mutate generated source as the durable source of truth.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md\"}\n26:   ],\n27:   \"metrics\": {\n28:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n29:     \"openQuestions\": 0,\n30:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n31:     \"keyFindings\": 8,\n32:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.69,\n33:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n34:       \"primaryDocs\": 20,\n35:       \"localFiles\": 3,\n36:       \"adjacentTools\": 3\n37:     }\n38:   },\n39:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n40:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n41:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n42:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1781420686076-jgor8g\",\n43:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n44:   \"generation\": 1,\n45:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-14T09:45:30Z\"\n46: }\n\n(End of file - total 46 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"summary\":\"Distinctive capabilities surveyed across v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-001\",\"iteration-002\",\"iteration-003\",\"iteration-004\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"summary\":\"Deduped against packet 005; net-new patterns isolated from Claude Design parity overlap.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-005\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"summary\":\"ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts recorded per local skill.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#7-ranked-net-new-ideas\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"summary\":\"Negative knowledge captured for hosted, platform, preset, and over-automation directions.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#10-eliminated-alternatives\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"summary\":\"Prioritized recommendation set produced for merge host.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#11-recommendations\"]}\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"F1\",\"title\":\"Pre-build direction gate\",\"summary\":\"Lovable and Subframe generate multiple visual directions before committing to a build; adapt as a brief-specific critique gate, not presets.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F2\",\"title\":\"Element-target feedback grammar\",\"summary\":\"v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe all let users point to/select/annotate a rendered element, then describe a scoped change.\",\"sources\":[\"https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F3\",\"title\":\"Design-system adherence scanner\",\"summary\":\"Lovable explicitly checks for raw colors, one-off values, inline overrides, and local component misuse; Figma Make guidelines document token pitfalls and don't-do rules.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F4\",\"title\":\"Editable plan artifact before build\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make plan mode creates a reviewable plan markdown file before code changes; local skills can borrow the small artifact pattern for complex design work.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F5\",\"title\":\"Presentational/generated boundary\",\"summary\":\"Subframe separates deterministic presentational code from wrapper-owned business logic; mcp-magicpath should make the same boundary explicit for installed/generated components.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F6\",\"title\":\"Guidelines as design-system context\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make kits and Lovable design systems put machine-readable rules near component/tokens; local skills can emit and consume compact guidelines without hosting a platform.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F7\",\"title\":\"Fidelity loop limitations\",\"summary\":\"Browser testing is useful for behavior and screenshots but not subtle color/detail judgment; completion gates should state this limitation.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F8\",\"title\":\"MCP/design-document access\",\"summary\":\"Subframe exposes pages, components, theme, and design documents through MCP; MagicPath remains CLI-only, so adopt the output-manifest idea rather than the server surface.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md\"]}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"summary\":\"Distinctive capabilities surveyed across v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-001\",\"iteration-002\",\"iteration-003\",\"iteration-004\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"summary\":\"Deduped against packet 005; net-new patterns isolated from Claude Design parity overlap.\",\"evidence\":[\"iteration-005\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"summary\":\"ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts recorded per local skill.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#7-ranked-net-new-ideas\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"summary\":\"Negative knowledge captured for hosted, platform, preset, and over-automation directions.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#10-eliminated-alternatives\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"summary\":\"Prioritized recommendation set produced for merge host.\",\"evidence\":[\"research.md#11-recommendations\"]}\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"F1\",\"title\":\"Pre-build direction gate\",\"summary\":\"Lovable and Subframe generate multiple visual directions before committing to a build; adapt as a brief-specific critique gate, not presets.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F2\",\"title\":\"Element-target feedback grammar\",\"summary\":\"v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe all let users point to/select/annotate a rendered element, then describe a scoped change.\",\"sources\":[\"https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F3\",\"title\":\"Design-system adherence scanner\",\"summary\":\"Lovable explicitly checks for raw colors, one-off values, inline overrides, and local component misuse; Figma Make guidelines document token pitfalls and don't-do rules.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\",\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F4\",\"title\":\"Editable plan artifact before build\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make plan mode creates a reviewable plan markdown file before code changes; local skills can borrow the small artifact pattern for complex design work.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F5\",\"title\":\"Presentational/generated boundary\",\"summary\":\"Subframe separates deterministic presentational code from wrapper-owned business logic; mcp-magicpath should make the same boundary explicit for installed/generated components.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md\",\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F6\",\"title\":\"Guidelines as design-system context\",\"summary\":\"Figma Make kits and Lovable design systems put machine-readable rules near component/tokens; local skills can emit and consume compact guidelines without hosting a platform.\",\"sources\":[\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make\",\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F7\",\"title\":\"Fidelity loop limitations\",\"summary\":\"Browser testing is useful for behavior and screenshots but not subtle color/detail judgment; completion gates should state this limitation.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md\"]},\n    {\"id\":\"F8\",\"title\":\"MCP/design-document access\",\"summary\":\"Subframe exposes pages, components, theme, and design documents through MCP; MagicPath remains CLI-only, so adopt the output-manifest idea rather than the server surface.\",\"sources\":[\"https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md\"]}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\"approach\":\"Hosted deployment/backend agent\",\"reason\":\"Platform scope; not local skill scope.\",\"evidence\":\"https://vercel.com/docs/v0\"},\n    {\"approach\":\"Preset palette/font/layout chooser\",\"reason\":\"Conflicts with anti-default design judgment.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md\"},\n    {\"approach\":\"MagicPath-owned git branch/PR management\",\"reason\":\"Belongs to sk-git, not mcp-magicpath.\",\"evidence\":\"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase\"},\n    {\"approach\":\"Automated subtle visual diff as sole quality gate\",\"reason\":\"Browser testing is documented as unreliable for subtle design details.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md\"},\n    {\"approach\":\"Two-way generated component source ownership\",\"reason\":\"Use generated source plus wrapper boundary; do not mutate generated source as the durable source of truth.\",\"evidence\":\"https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md\"}\n  ],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n    \"keyFindings\": 8,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0.69,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {\n      \"primaryDocs\": 20,\n      \"localFiles\": 3,\n      \"adjacentTools\": 3\n    }\n  },\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1781420686076-jgor8g\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-14T09:45:30Z\"\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":46,"totalLines":46,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1782532788621,"end":1782532788634}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db3c8b307f56147016a3f4ab4728881918a5e1fd679b37128"}},"id":"prt_f073bd17b001uTX85KEska3Tx5","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f073b88ca0015DUh7WpkP1fCum"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532788638,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_G86whCLvGk2aqr9HfISsTMCq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/research.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Lineage Research: Competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-design-interface and mcp-magicpath (gpt55fast)\"\n3: description: \"gpt55fast fan-out lineage synthesis for packet 006: competitor AI UI/design tool ideas from v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools. Research-only; no skill implementation changes.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"gpt55fast competitor design tool research\"\n6:   - \"v0 lovable figma make subframe lineage\"\n7:   - \"sk-design-interface mcp-magicpath competitor ideas\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: ---\n11: \n12: # Lineage Research: Competitor AI Design-Tool Ideas (gpt55fast)\n13: \n14: This is the `gpt55fast` lineage synthesis for packet 006. It ran five iterations to the configured cap and wrote only inside the lineage artifact directory.\n15: \n16: ## 1. Executive Summary\n17: \n18: The net-new competitor lesson is not \"build a hosted design product.\" The useful patterns are smaller and more transferable:\n19: \n20: 1. **Pre-build direction gate**: show 2-3 brief-specific directions before building when the visual axis is open.\n21: 2. **Element-target feedback grammar**: selected element / annotation / screenshot / prompt / apply boundary is now a standard interaction pattern across v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe.\n22: 3. **Design-system adherence scanner**: raw colors, one-off values, inline styles, and custom component bypasses should become explicit violation classes.\n23: 4. **Editable plan/guidelines artifact**: complex design work benefits from a short reviewable plan or guidelines file before code/canvas generation.\n24: 5. **Presentational/generated boundary**: generated visual layer and app/business logic must have a clear wrapper/adaptation seam.\n25: \n26: Packet 005 already covered the broad Claude Design parity loop. This lineage sharpens the tactical controls around that loop.\n27: \n28: ## 2. Method and Provenance\n29: \n30: | Item | Value |\n31: | --- | --- |\n32: | Lineage | `gpt55fast` |\n33: | Executor | `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` |\n34: | Iterations | 5/5, stopped at maxIterations |\n35: | Primary competitor docs | v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe |\n36: | Adjacent docs | Anima, Builder, Framer surface checks |\n37: | Local evidence | `sk-design-interface` SKILL.md, `mcp-magicpath` SKILL.md, packet 005 synthesis |\n38: | Write boundary | Artifact directory only; parent spec write-back skipped/deferred |\n39: \n40: ## 3. Competitor Capability Matrix\n41: \n42: | Tool | Distinctive design-relevant capability | Local transfer |\n43: | --- | --- | --- |\n44: | v0 | Design Mode edits live preview elements with visual controls, natural-language selected-element prompts, pending before/after state, and diffable applied versions. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] | ADOPT element-target feedback grammar for `mcp-magicpath`; ADAPT selected-render critique for `sk-design-interface`. |\n45: | v0 | Figma link import extracts layout plus design tokens; docs recommend component-first decomposition. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/figma] | ADAPT into design-context decomposition guidance. |\n46: | v0 | Registries pass components, blocks, and tokens as AI-native design-system context. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-systems] | ADAPT as compact local context/handoff packet, not hosted registry. |\n47: | Lovable | Three rendered design directions appear before full build for open-ended visual prompts; refinements are capped before submitting. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] | ADAPT as anti-default direction gate for `sk-design-interface`; avoid presets. |\n48: | Lovable | Preview toolbar supports select, inline text edit, draw annotation, comments, and queued changes. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] | ADOPT as MagicPath revision-intake grammar. |\n49: | Lovable | Design-system attach includes schema/docs and adherence scans for raw colors, one-off values, inline overrides, and local component bypass. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] | ADOPT violation taxonomy for both skills. |\n50: | Lovable | Browser testing captures screenshots and behavior but is not reliable for subtle design/color differences. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] | ADOPT limitation statement in fidelity verification. |\n51: | Figma Make | Plan mode writes editable `plan.md` before build. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] | ADAPT as optional plan artifact for complex design/canvas tasks. |\n52: | Figma Make | Make kits package npm packages, library styles, and guidelines. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] | ADAPT as local design-context kit/guidelines input. |\n53: | Figma Make | Local-codebase beta uses real app preview, annotations, point edits, local commits, and PRs. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] | ADAPT reversible edit provenance; SKIP Git/PR ownership in MagicPath. |\n54: | Subframe | Deterministic presentational React code; no LLM in codegen path. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md] | ADOPT explicit generated/presentational boundary; do not overclaim determinism. |\n55: | Subframe | Components sync one-way; wrapper `index.tsx` owns business logic. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | ADOPT wrapper/adaptation boundary for MagicPath installed components. |\n56: | Subframe | MCP exposes pages, components, theme, and design documents to AI coding assistants. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md] | ADAPT as handoff/design-document manifest; do not add a new MCP server. |\n57: \n58: ## 4. Dedup Against Packet 005\n59: \n60: Packet 005 already recommended a shared protocol: design-context snapshot, iteration ledger, handoff manifest, MagicPath fidelity verification, and design-system inheritance. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/005-claude-design-parity-research/research/research.md]\n61: \n62: This lineage does not duplicate those as top-line novelty. It adds sharper mechanisms:\n63: \n64: | New or sharper idea | Relationship to packet 005 |\n65: | --- | --- |\n66: | Pre-build direction gate | Net-new before-build complement to post-build fidelity loop. |\n67: | Element-target feedback grammar | Sharper operational shape for iteration ledger rows. |\n68: | Design-system adherence scanner | Sharper validation taxonomy for design-system inheritance. |\n69: | Editable plan/guidelines artifact | Sharper setup artifact before complex generation. |\n70: | Presentational/generated wrapper boundary | Sharper handoff rule for generated component code. |\n71: | Browser-testing limitation caveat | Corrects overconfidence risk in fidelity verification. |\n72: \n73: ## 5. Design Principles for Local Adoption\n74: \n75: - Preserve `sk-design-interface` as a judgment skill, not a generator or preset picker. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md]\n76: - Preserve `mcp-magicpath` as a CLI/canvas operator, not a hosted product or git workflow owner. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md]\n77: - Prefer small protocol additions over new infrastructure.\n78: - Treat SKIP as success when a competitor feature would dilute local boundaries.\n79: \n80: ## 6. Net-New Ideas\n81: \n82: | Idea | Evidence | Why it matters |\n83: | --- | --- | --- |\n84: | Direction gate | Lovable three previews; Subframe 1-4 variations. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md] | Reduces first-build misses and forces deliberate visual direction before code/canvas output. |\n85: | Element-target grammar | v0 selected elements; Lovable toolbar; Figma Make annotations; Subframe quick edits. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md] | Makes feedback precise and auditable. |\n86: | Adherence scanner | Lovable design systems; Figma Make kit guidelines. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] | Turns vague \"use the design system\" into explicit violation checks. |\n87: | Editable plan/guidelines artifact | Figma Make plan mode and guidelines. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make] | Supports complex work without changing runtime architecture. |\n88: | Generated/presentational boundary | Subframe components/pages and sync docs. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/design-to-code.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | Prevents generated component drift and clarifies what app code may safely edit. |\n89: \n90: ## 7. Ranked Net-New Ideas\n91: \n92: | Rank | Idea | `sk-design-interface` verdict | `mcp-magicpath` verdict | Rationale |\n93: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n94: | P1 | Element-target feedback grammar | ADAPT | ADOPT | `sk` uses it as critique language; `mp` can operationalize selected element, annotation, screenshot, prompt, and verification fields. |\n95: | P1 | Design-system adherence scanner | ADOPT | ADOPT | Both skills need explicit violation classes when a system exists. |\n96: | P1 | Presentational/generated boundary | ADAPT | ADOPT | `sk` states visual direction only; `mp` needs generated vs wrapper/adaptation file rules. |\n97: | P2 | Pre-build direction gate | ADOPT with guardrails | ADAPT | Strong for open visual tasks; keep it brief-specific, never a preset menu. |\n98: | P2 | Editable plan/guidelines artifact | ADAPT | ADAPT | Useful for complex/high-blast tasks; too heavy for simple component work. |\n99: | P2 | Browser-testing limitation caveat | ADOPT | ADOPT | Prevents false completion claims from screenshots alone. |\n100: | P3 | AI-native design-document manifest | ADAPT | ADAPT | Subframe MCP design docs suggest richer handoff docs; use manifest, not new server. |\n101: | P3 | Figma/preview layer round trip | SKIP | SKIP unless MagicPath exposes equivalent | Useful product feature but not currently available in local CLI scope. |\n102: \n103: ## 8. Recommendations for sk-design-interface\n104: \n105: | Priority | Verdict | Recommendation | Guardrail |\n106: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n107: | P1 | ADOPT | Add a design-system adherence checklist when a system is present: semantic tokens first, no raw colors, no arbitrary spacing, no local component bypass, no inline override without reason. | Do not become a linter; this is design judgment plus evidence. |\n108: | P1 | ADAPT | Add element-target feedback vocabulary for rendered self-critique: selected region, observed issue, intended design principle, proposed one-change revision. | Do not require a render for every design task. |\n109: | P2 | ADOPT | Add a brief-specific direction gate for open-ended visual work: 2-3 direction sketches, critique against AI defaults, recommend one. | No reusable style presets; no curated palette menu. |\n110: | P2 | ADAPT | Emit optional guideline snippets for complex handoffs: token quirks, do-not rules, typography/spacing priorities. | Keep concise; more context is not always better. |\n111: | P3 | ADAPT | State when output is visual direction only and what app logic remains out of scope. | Implementation remains `sk-code` / `mcp-magicpath`. |\n112: \n113: ## 9. Recommendations for mcp-magicpath\n114: \n115: | Priority | Verdict | Recommendation | Guardrail |\n116: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n117: | P1 | ADOPT | Add a MagicPath revision-intake grammar: target element/component, visual evidence, requested change, scope, expected verification, and whether feedback is broad or targeted. | Do not infer ambiguous targets; ask or inspect. |\n118: | P1 | ADOPT | Add generated-vs-adapted source boundary to install/author flows: generated component source, wrapper/adaptation files, safe edit points, and remaining business logic. | Never copy generated markup instead of importing installed components. |\n119: | P1 | ADOPT | Add design-system adherence scan after generated output when project/theme context exists: raw color, arbitrary spacing, inline style, unapproved component, token misuse. | Keep mechanical; design choices still route to `sk-design-interface`. |\n120: | P2 | ADAPT | For complex canvas authoring, create a short plan/guidelines block before `code start`/`code submit`. | Skip for simple exact component operations. |\n121: | P2 | ADAPT | Batch queued visual edits into one submit/verify cycle when safe. | Do not hide partial changes from the user. |\n122: | P3 | SKIP | Do not own Git branch/PR flows, local repo setup scripts, public publishing, or backend setup. | Route Git to `sk-git`; route app code to `sk-code`. |\n123: \n124: ## 10. Eliminated Alternatives\n125: \n126: | Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n127: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n128: | Hosted full-stack app/deployment agent | v0/Lovable platform scope exceeds these two skills. | [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/introduction/welcome.md] | 1, 5 |\n129: | Preset palette/font/layout chooser | Conflicts with `sk-design-interface` anti-default mandate. | [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md] | 2, 5 |\n130: | MagicPath-owned Git branch/PR workflow | Belongs to `sk-git` or external workflow, not MagicPath CLI. | [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] | 3, 5 |\n131: | Subtle visual diff automation as sole quality gate | Browser testing docs say it is unreliable for subtle visual design details/color differences. | [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] | 2, 5 |\n132: | Two-way generated component source ownership | Subframe uses one-way sync and wrapper boundaries; local generated files should not become ambiguous source-of-truth. | [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | 4, 5 |\n133: | Live multiplayer canvas, public publishing, billing/admin governance | Hosted product capabilities, not lean CLI-skill responsibilities. | [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make] | 3, 5 |\n134: \n135: ## 11. Recommendations\n136: \n137: 1. **Implement first as protocol text, not code**: add a shared reference describing element-target feedback, adherence checks, and generated/presentational boundaries.\n138: 2. **Update `sk-design-interface` next**: direction gate and adherence checklist are small additions aligned with the existing two-pass process.\n139: 3. **Update `mcp-magicpath` after that**: revision-intake grammar, wrapper boundary, post-submit adherence scan, and optional complex-task plan block.\n140: 4. **Keep packet 005 as the broad loop**: this packet should refine operational mechanics, not replace the context/iteration/handoff protocol.\n141: \n142: ## 12. Open Questions\n143: \n144: - How much of MagicPath's current `code submit --wait` output can be inspected automatically for raw colors, arbitrary values, and generated/adapted boundary violations?\n145: - Does MagicPath expose enough preview/selection metadata to support a true selected-element feedback grammar, or should the first version be text/screenshot based?\n146: - When the sibling opus lineage completes, does it agree that the direction gate and adherence scanner are the main net-new ideas?\n147: \n148: ## 13. Cross-Lineage Notes\n149: \n150: At the time this lineage synthesized, `opus48-claude2` had only config/strategy visible and no completed iteration artifacts. Cross-lineage reconciliation is therefore deferred to the host merge step. This lineage is ready to merge and highlights expected comparison points:\n151: \n152: - Does the sibling also prioritize element-target feedback?\n153: - Does it treat the direction gate as ADOPT or too preset-like?\n154: - Does it agree on the generated/presentational boundary for MagicPath?\n155: - Does it identify any competitor feature stronger than the adherence scanner?\n156: \n157: ## 14. Source Notes and Limitations\n158: \n159: - Primary docs were used where possible.\n160: - Some adjacent-product docs were broad or marketing-heavy and are not load-bearing for top recommendations.\n161: - Browser/WebFetch pages do not provide stable line numbers; citations use URLs.\n162: - Local file evidence uses exact file paths from reads.\n163: \n164: ## 15. References\n165: \n166: - v0 overview, Design Mode, Design Systems, Figma integration: [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-systems] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/figma]\n167: - Lovable design guidance, preview toolbar, browser testing, design systems, knowledge, skills: [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/knowledge.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/skills.md]\n168: - Figma Make overview, plan mode, Make kits, design-system package, guidelines, local codebase: [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/35946832653975-Use-your-design-system-package-in-Make-kits] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase]\n169: - Subframe overview, code generation, design-to-code, syncing components, Ask AI, quick edits, theme export, MCP server: [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/overview.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/design-to-code.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/theme/exporting-theme.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md]\n170: - Adjacent sources: [SOURCE: https://docs.animaapp.com/docs/getting-started] [SOURCE: https://www.builder.io/c/docs/import-from-figma] [SOURCE: https://www.framer.com/]\n171: - Local sources: [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/005-claude-design-parity-research/research/research.md]\n172: \n173: ## 16. Convergence Report\n174: \n175: - Stop reason: maxIterationsReached.\n176: - Total iterations: 5.\n177: - Questions answered: 5 / 5.\n178: - Remaining questions: 0 for this lineage; cross-lineage merge remains.\n179: - Average newInfoRatio trend: [1.00, 0.82, 0.72, 0.58, 0.31].\n180: - Quality gates: pass for source diversity, negative knowledge, local-scope guardrails, and per-skill verdicts.\n181: - Graph gates: not applicable; no graph events emitted.\n182: \n183: ## 17. Final Lineage Output\n184: \n185: This lineage recommends a focused follow-up implementation packet that updates both skills with protocol-level guidance first. The safest P1 bundle is:\n186: \n187: - Element-target feedback grammar.\n188: - Design-system adherence violation taxonomy.\n189: - Generated/presentational wrapper boundary for MagicPath.\n190: - Direction gate for `sk-design-interface`, guarded against presets.\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Lineage Research: Competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-design-interface and mcp-magicpath (gpt55fast)\"\ndescription: \"gpt55fast fan-out lineage synthesis for packet 006: competitor AI UI/design tool ideas from v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools. Research-only; no skill implementation changes.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"gpt55fast competitor design tool research\"\n  - \"v0 lovable figma make subframe lineage\"\n  - \"sk-design-interface mcp-magicpath competitor ideas\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Lineage Research: Competitor AI Design-Tool Ideas (gpt55fast)\n\nThis is the `gpt55fast` lineage synthesis for packet 006. It ran five iterations to the configured cap and wrote only inside the lineage artifact directory.\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nThe net-new competitor lesson is not \"build a hosted design product.\" The useful patterns are smaller and more transferable:\n\n1. **Pre-build direction gate**: show 2-3 brief-specific directions before building when the visual axis is open.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/research.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Lineage Research: Competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-design-interface and mcp-magicpath (gpt55fast)\"\ndescription: \"gpt55fast fan-out lineage synthesis for packet 006: competitor AI UI/design tool ideas from v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and adjacent tools. Research-only; no skill implementation changes.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"gpt55fast competitor design tool research\"\n  - \"v0 lovable figma make subframe lineage\"\n  - \"sk-design-interface mcp-magicpath competitor ideas\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Lineage Research: Competitor AI Design-Tool Ideas (gpt55fast)\n\nThis is the `gpt55fast` lineage synthesis for packet 006. It ran five iterations to the configured cap and wrote only inside the lineage artifact directory.\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nThe net-new competitor lesson is not \"build a hosted design product.\" The useful patterns are smaller and more transferable:\n\n1. **Pre-build direction gate**: show 2-3 brief-specific directions before building when the visual axis is open.\n2. **Element-target feedback grammar**: selected element / annotation / screenshot / prompt / apply boundary is now a standard interaction pattern across v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe.\n3. **Design-system adherence scanner**: raw colors, one-off values, inline styles, and custom component bypasses should become explicit violation classes.\n4. **Editable plan/guidelines artifact**: complex design work benefits from a short reviewable plan or guidelines file before code/canvas generation.\n5. **Presentational/generated boundary**: generated visual layer and app/business logic must have a clear wrapper/adaptation seam.\n\nPacket 005 already covered the broad Claude Design parity loop. This lineage sharpens the tactical controls around that loop.\n\n## 2. Method and Provenance\n\n| Item | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| Lineage | `gpt55fast` |\n| Executor | `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast` |\n| Iterations | 5/5, stopped at maxIterations |\n| Primary competitor docs | v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe |\n| Adjacent docs | Anima, Builder, Framer surface checks |\n| Local evidence | `sk-design-interface` SKILL.md, `mcp-magicpath` SKILL.md, packet 005 synthesis |\n| Write boundary | Artifact directory only; parent spec write-back skipped/deferred |\n\n## 3. Competitor Capability Matrix\n\n| Tool | Distinctive design-relevant capability | Local transfer |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| v0 | Design Mode edits live preview elements with visual controls, natural-language selected-element prompts, pending before/after state, and diffable applied versions. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] | ADOPT element-target feedback grammar for `mcp-magicpath`; ADAPT selected-render critique for `sk-design-interface`. |\n| v0 | Figma link import extracts layout plus design tokens; docs recommend component-first decomposition. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/figma] | ADAPT into design-context decomposition guidance. |\n| v0 | Registries pass components, blocks, and tokens as AI-native design-system context. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-systems] | ADAPT as compact local context/handoff packet, not hosted registry. |\n| Lovable | Three rendered design directions appear before full build for open-ended visual prompts; refinements are capped before submitting. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] | ADAPT as anti-default direction gate for `sk-design-interface`; avoid presets. |\n| Lovable | Preview toolbar supports select, inline text edit, draw annotation, comments, and queued changes. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] | ADOPT as MagicPath revision-intake grammar. |\n| Lovable | Design-system attach includes schema/docs and adherence scans for raw colors, one-off values, inline overrides, and local component bypass. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] | ADOPT violation taxonomy for both skills. |\n| Lovable | Browser testing captures screenshots and behavior but is not reliable for subtle design/color differences. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] | ADOPT limitation statement in fidelity verification. |\n| Figma Make | Plan mode writes editable `plan.md` before build. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] | ADAPT as optional plan artifact for complex design/canvas tasks. |\n| Figma Make | Make kits package npm packages, library styles, and guidelines. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] | ADAPT as local design-context kit/guidelines input. |\n| Figma Make | Local-codebase beta uses real app preview, annotations, point edits, local commits, and PRs. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] | ADAPT reversible edit provenance; SKIP Git/PR ownership in MagicPath. |\n| Subframe | Deterministic presentational React code; no LLM in codegen path. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md] | ADOPT explicit generated/presentational boundary; do not overclaim determinism. |\n| Subframe | Components sync one-way; wrapper `index.tsx` owns business logic. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | ADOPT wrapper/adaptation boundary for MagicPath installed components. |\n| Subframe | MCP exposes pages, components, theme, and design documents to AI coding assistants. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md] | ADAPT as handoff/design-document manifest; do not add a new MCP server. |\n\n## 4. Dedup Against Packet 005\n\nPacket 005 already recommended a shared protocol: design-context snapshot, iteration ledger, handoff manifest, MagicPath fidelity verification, and design-system inheritance. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/005-claude-design-parity-research/research/research.md]\n\nThis lineage does not duplicate those as top-line novelty. It adds sharper mechanisms:\n\n| New or sharper idea | Relationship to packet 005 |\n| --- | --- |\n| Pre-build direction gate | Net-new before-build complement to post-build fidelity loop. |\n| Element-target feedback grammar | Sharper operational shape for iteration ledger rows. |\n| Design-system adherence scanner | Sharper validation taxonomy for design-system inheritance. |\n| Editable plan/guidelines artifact | Sharper setup artifact before complex generation. |\n| Presentational/generated wrapper boundary | Sharper handoff rule for generated component code. |\n| Browser-testing limitation caveat | Corrects overconfidence risk in fidelity verification. |\n\n## 5. Design Principles for Local Adoption\n\n- Preserve `sk-design-interface` as a judgment skill, not a generator or preset picker. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md]\n- Preserve `mcp-magicpath` as a CLI/canvas operator, not a hosted product or git workflow owner. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md]\n- Prefer small protocol additions over new infrastructure.\n- Treat SKIP as success when a competitor feature would dilute local boundaries.\n\n## 6. Net-New Ideas\n\n| Idea | Evidence | Why it matters |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direction gate | Lovable three previews; Subframe 1-4 variations. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md] | Reduces first-build misses and forces deliberate visual direction before code/canvas output. |\n| Element-target grammar | v0 selected elements; Lovable toolbar; Figma Make annotations; Subframe quick edits. [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md] | Makes feedback precise and auditable. |\n| Adherence scanner | Lovable design systems; Figma Make kit guidelines. [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] | Turns vague \"use the design system\" into explicit violation checks. |\n| Editable plan/guidelines artifact | Figma Make plan mode and guidelines. [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make] | Supports complex work without changing runtime architecture. |\n| Generated/presentational boundary | Subframe components/pages and sync docs. [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/design-to-code.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | Prevents generated component drift and clarifies what app code may safely edit. |\n\n## 7. Ranked Net-New Ideas\n\n| Rank | Idea | `sk-design-interface` verdict | `mcp-magicpath` verdict | Rationale |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| P1 | Element-target feedback grammar | ADAPT | ADOPT | `sk` uses it as critique language; `mp` can operationalize selected element, annotation, screenshot, prompt, and verification fields. |\n| P1 | Design-system adherence scanner | ADOPT | ADOPT | Both skills need explicit violation classes when a system exists. |\n| P1 | Presentational/generated boundary | ADAPT | ADOPT | `sk` states visual direction only; `mp` needs generated vs wrapper/adaptation file rules. |\n| P2 | Pre-build direction gate | ADOPT with guardrails | ADAPT | Strong for open visual tasks; keep it brief-specific, never a preset menu. |\n| P2 | Editable plan/guidelines artifact | ADAPT | ADAPT | Useful for complex/high-blast tasks; too heavy for simple component work. |\n| P2 | Browser-testing limitation caveat | ADOPT | ADOPT | Prevents false completion claims from screenshots alone. |\n| P3 | AI-native design-document manifest | ADAPT | ADAPT | Subframe MCP design docs suggest richer handoff docs; use manifest, not new server. |\n| P3 | Figma/preview layer round trip | SKIP | SKIP unless MagicPath exposes equivalent | Useful product feature but not currently available in local CLI scope. |\n\n## 8. Recommendations for sk-design-interface\n\n| Priority | Verdict | Recommendation | Guardrail |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| P1 | ADOPT | Add a design-system adherence checklist when a system is present: semantic tokens first, no raw colors, no arbitrary spacing, no local component bypass, no inline override without reason. | Do not become a linter; this is design judgment plus evidence. |\n| P1 | ADAPT | Add element-target feedback vocabulary for rendered self-critique: selected region, observed issue, intended design principle, proposed one-change revision. | Do not require a render for every design task. |\n| P2 | ADOPT | Add a brief-specific direction gate for open-ended visual work: 2-3 direction sketches, critique against AI defaults, recommend one. | No reusable style presets; no curated palette menu. |\n| P2 | ADAPT | Emit optional guideline snippets for complex handoffs: token quirks, do-not rules, typography/spacing priorities. | Keep concise; more context is not always better. |\n| P3 | ADAPT | State when output is visual direction only and what app logic remains out of scope. | Implementation remains `sk-code` / `mcp-magicpath`. |\n\n## 9. Recommendations for mcp-magicpath\n\n| Priority | Verdict | Recommendation | Guardrail |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| P1 | ADOPT | Add a MagicPath revision-intake grammar: target element/component, visual evidence, requested change, scope, expected verification, and whether feedback is broad or targeted. | Do not infer ambiguous targets; ask or inspect. |\n| P1 | ADOPT | Add generated-vs-adapted source boundary to install/author flows: generated component source, wrapper/adaptation files, safe edit points, and remaining business logic. | Never copy generated markup instead of importing installed components. |\n| P1 | ADOPT | Add design-system adherence scan after generated output when project/theme context exists: raw color, arbitrary spacing, inline style, unapproved component, token misuse. | Keep mechanical; design choices still route to `sk-design-interface`. |\n| P2 | ADAPT | For complex canvas authoring, create a short plan/guidelines block before `code start`/`code submit`. | Skip for simple exact component operations. |\n| P2 | ADAPT | Batch queued visual edits into one submit/verify cycle when safe. | Do not hide partial changes from the user. |\n| P3 | SKIP | Do not own Git branch/PR flows, local repo setup scripts, public publishing, or backend setup. | Route Git to `sk-git`; route app code to `sk-code`. |\n\n## 10. Eliminated Alternatives\n\n| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Hosted full-stack app/deployment agent | v0/Lovable platform scope exceeds these two skills. | [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/introduction/welcome.md] | 1, 5 |\n| Preset palette/font/layout chooser | Conflicts with `sk-design-interface` anti-default mandate. | [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md] | 2, 5 |\n| MagicPath-owned Git branch/PR workflow | Belongs to `sk-git` or external workflow, not MagicPath CLI. | [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase] | 3, 5 |\n| Subtle visual diff automation as sole quality gate | Browser testing docs say it is unreliable for subtle visual design details/color differences. | [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] | 2, 5 |\n| Two-way generated component source ownership | Subframe uses one-way sync and wrapper boundaries; local generated files should not become ambiguous source-of-truth. | [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] | 4, 5 |\n| Live multiplayer canvas, public publishing, billing/admin governance | Hosted product capabilities, not lean CLI-skill responsibilities. | [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make] | 3, 5 |\n\n## 11. Recommendations\n\n1. **Implement first as protocol text, not code**: add a shared reference describing element-target feedback, adherence checks, and generated/presentational boundaries.\n2. **Update `sk-design-interface` next**: direction gate and adherence checklist are small additions aligned with the existing two-pass process.\n3. **Update `mcp-magicpath` after that**: revision-intake grammar, wrapper boundary, post-submit adherence scan, and optional complex-task plan block.\n4. **Keep packet 005 as the broad loop**: this packet should refine operational mechanics, not replace the context/iteration/handoff protocol.\n\n## 12. Open Questions\n\n- How much of MagicPath's current `code submit --wait` output can be inspected automatically for raw colors, arbitrary values, and generated/adapted boundary violations?\n- Does MagicPath expose enough preview/selection metadata to support a true selected-element feedback grammar, or should the first version be text/screenshot based?\n- When the sibling opus lineage completes, does it agree that the direction gate and adherence scanner are the main net-new ideas?\n\n## 13. Cross-Lineage Notes\n\nAt the time this lineage synthesized, `opus48-claude2` had only config/strategy visible and no completed iteration artifacts. Cross-lineage reconciliation is therefore deferred to the host merge step. This lineage is ready to merge and highlights expected comparison points:\n\n- Does the sibling also prioritize element-target feedback?\n- Does it treat the direction gate as ADOPT or too preset-like?\n- Does it agree on the generated/presentational boundary for MagicPath?\n- Does it identify any competitor feature stronger than the adherence scanner?\n\n## 14. Source Notes and Limitations\n\n- Primary docs were used where possible.\n- Some adjacent-product docs were broad or marketing-heavy and are not load-bearing for top recommendations.\n- Browser/WebFetch pages do not provide stable line numbers; citations use URLs.\n- Local file evidence uses exact file paths from reads.\n\n## 15. References\n\n- v0 overview, Design Mode, Design Systems, Figma integration: [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-mode] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/design-systems] [SOURCE: https://vercel.com/docs/v0/figma]\n- Lovable design guidance, preview toolbar, browser testing, design systems, knowledge, skills: [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-guidance.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/preview-toolbar.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/browser-testing.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/design-systems.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/knowledge.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.lovable.dev/features/skills.md]\n- Figma Make overview, plan mode, Make kits, design-system package, guidelines, local codebase: [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40830441709719-Use-plan-mode-in-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39241689698839-Get-started-with-Make-kits] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/35946832653975-Use-your-design-system-package-in-Make-kits] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33665861260823-Add-guidelines-to-Figma-Make] [SOURCE: https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40775535020695-Make-in-your-local-codebase]\n- Subframe overview, code generation, design-to-code, syncing components, Ask AI, quick edits, theme export, MCP server: [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/overview.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/code-generation.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/design-to-code.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/concepts/syncing-components.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/prompt-to-design.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/ask-ai/making-quick-edits.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/learn/theme/exporting-theme.md] [SOURCE: https://docs.subframe.com/guides/mcp-server.md]\n- Adjacent sources: [SOURCE: https://docs.animaapp.com/docs/getting-started] [SOURCE: https://www.builder.io/c/docs/import-from-figma] [SOURCE: https://www.framer.com/]\n- Local sources: [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/SKILL.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/mcp-magicpath/SKILL.md] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/005-claude-design-parity-research/research/research.md]\n\n## 16. Convergence Report\n\n- Stop reason: maxIterationsReached.\n- Total iterations: 5.\n- Questions answered: 5 / 5.\n- Remaining questions: 0 for this lineage; cross-lineage merge remains.\n- Average newInfoRatio trend: [1.00, 0.82, 0.72, 0.58, 0.31].\n- Quality gates: pass for source diversity, negative knowledge, local-scope guardrails, and per-skill verdicts.\n- Graph gates: not applicable; no graph events emitted.\n\n## 17. Final Lineage Output\n\nThis lineage recommends a focused follow-up implementation packet that updates both skills with protocol-level guidance first. The safest P1 bundle is:\n\n- Element-target feedback grammar.\n- Design-system adherence violation taxonomy.\n- Generated/presentational wrapper boundary for MagicPath.\n- Direction gate for `sk-design-interface`, guarded against presets.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":190,"totalLines":190,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/143-sk-design-interface/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/research.md","time":{"start":1782532788631,"end":1782532788637}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0db3c8b307f56147016a3f4ab4728c81918de02e26f745f4da"}},"id":"prt_f073bd18e0019Wjghi3ie1CeY4","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c97ffeoYuqUQ1KEMV7ea","messageID":"msg_f073b88ca0015DUh7WpkP1fCum"}}
