\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"reason\":\"operator constrained this fan-out lineage to write only inside artifact_dir; parent spec.md pre-init and post-synthesis write-back were skipped\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:06Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"router_replay_sample\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"promptClass\":\"full-audit-score\",\"parseable\":true,\"intents\":[\"AUDIT_CONTRACT\"],\"resources\":[\"references/corpus_map.md\",\"references/audit_contract.md\",\"assets/audit_report_template.md\"],\"missingResources\":[],\"scores\":[{\"intent\":\"AUDIT_CONTRACT\",\"score\":20}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:07Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"router_replay_sample\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"promptClass\":\"ai-fingerprint\",\"parseable\":true,\"intents\":[\"ANTI_PATTERNS_PRODUCTION\"],\"resources\":[\"references/corpus_map.md\",\"references/anti_patterns_production.md\",\"references/ai_fingerprint_tells.md\"],\"missingResources\":[],\"scores\":[{\"intent\":\"ANTI_PATTERNS_PRODUCTION\",\"score\":8}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:08Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"router_replay_sample\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"promptClass\":\"a11y-performance\",\"parseable\":true,\"intents\":[\"ACCESSIBILITY_PERFORMANCE\"],\"resources\":[\"references/corpus_map.md\",\"references/accessibility_performance.md\",\"assets/a11y_quick_fixes.md\"],\"missingResources\":[],\"scores\":[{\"intent\":\"ACCESSIBILITY_PERFORMANCE\",\"score\":20}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:09Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"router_replay_sample\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"promptClass\":\"transform-after-audit\",\"parseable\":true,\"intents\":[\"AUDIT_CONTRACT\",\"TRANSFORM_REMEDIATION\"],\"resources\":[\"references/corpus_map.md\",\"references/audit_contract.md\",\"assets/audit_report_template.md\",\"references/transform_remediation.md\"],\"missingResources\":[],\"scores\":[{\"intent\":\"AUDIT_CONTRACT\",\"score\":4},{\"intent\":\"TRANSFORM_REMEDIATION\",\"score\":4}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:10Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"router_replay_sample\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"promptClass\":\"screenshot-evidence\",\"parseable\":true,\"intents\":[\"EVIDENCE_CAPTURE\"],\"resources\":[\"references/corpus_map.md\",\"references/evidence_capture.md\"],\"missingResources\":[],\"scores\":[{\"intent\":\"EVIDENCE_CAPTURE\",\"score\":6}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:01:11Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"iteration\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Current audit inventory and maturity baseline\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass established that audit already has strong severity, scoring, evidence, a11y, hardening, AI tell and transform materials; improvements must be narrow and operational.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q1\",\"Q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q1 partly\",\"Q2 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:03:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit_contract.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/corpus_map.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Evidence capture, report template, and audit deliverable ergonomics\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.72,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Evidence_capture and report template exist, but the workflow lacks a filled evidence worksheet that carries confirmed/inferred/not-assessed labels through every dimension and finding.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\",\"Q4\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2 partly\",\"Q4 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:06:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/evidence_capture.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/audit_report_template.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Mode A router replay and parseable routing defects\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.58,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Router replay is parseable, but it exposed two high-leverage defects: the pseudocode keyword loop is not executable as written, and the shared register ALWAYS load is absent from replay resources.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q3\",\"Q5\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q3\",\"Q5 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:09:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"stdout:router-replay full-audit-score\",\"stdout:router-replay ai-fingerprint\",\"stdout:router-replay a11y-performance\",\"stdout:router-replay transform-after-audit\",\"stdout:router-replay screenshot-evidence\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"iteration\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Accessibility, performance, and quick-fix handoff\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"A11y/performance thresholds and quick-fix snippets are strong; the useful improvement is a report-to-backlog handoff that turns accepted findings into implementation tasks without making audit implement them.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q4\",\"Q6\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q4 partly\",\"Q6 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:12:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/accessibility_performance.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/assets/a11y_quick_fixes.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":5,\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Hardening matrix and production-readiness probes\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.36,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Hardening matrix is detailed, but needs a small run-log asset so probes are recorded as pass/fail/skip with evidence instead of summarized from memory.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\",\"Q4\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2 partly\",\"Q4 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:15:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/hardening_edge_cases.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/critique_hardening.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":6,\"iteration\":6,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"AI fingerprint tells, anti-pattern scoring, and calibration\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.28,\"noveltyJustification\":\"AI tell catalog is unusually concrete; the gap is a dimension-score calibration ladder that maps tell counts, systemic spread and user impact into Anti-Patterns 0-4 scores.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\",\"Q5\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2 partly\",\"Q5 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:18:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/ai_fingerprint_tells.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti_patterns_production.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":7,\"iteration\":7,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Register-gated transform remediation and cross-mode ownership\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.21,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Transform remediation already routes bolder/quieter/distill/redesign well, but its dependency on the shared register makes the missing router load higher priority.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\",\"Q3\",\"Q6\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2\",\"Q3\",\"Q6 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:21:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/transform_remediation.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/register.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":8,\"iteration\":8,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Manual testing playbook and absent audit benchmark artifacts\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.14,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Manual scenarios exist, but no design-audit benchmark report directory was present under packet 014 in this checkout, so reproducible routing fixtures are a direct next improvement.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q5\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q5\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:24:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\"glob:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-audit/**\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":9,\"iteration\":9,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Negative knowledge and implementation boundaries\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.07,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Most apparent expansions are duplicates or scope creep; negative knowledge is itself a high-value output for this mature skill.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q6\",\"Q7\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q6\",\"Q7 partly\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:27:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":10,\"iteration\":10,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Prioritized synthesis and convergence check\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.03,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Final pass converged on a narrow improvement stack: router correctness, register loading, benchmark fixtures, evidence worksheets, backlog handoff and score calibration.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q1\",\"Q2\",\"Q3\",\"Q4\",\"Q5\",\"Q6\",\"Q7\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q1\",\"Q2\",\"Q3\",\"Q4\",\"Q5\",\"Q6\",\"Q7\"],\"durationMs\":300000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:30:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1,\"sources\":[\"file:research.md\",\"file:deep-research-findings-registry.json\"]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"answeredCount\":7,\"totalQuestions\":7,\"stopReason\":\"converged_at_max_iterations\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:31:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-avrwmk\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast audit lineage\n+\n+## Charter\n+\n+Produce prioritized, evidence-backed improvements for `sk-design` audit mode, constrained to research artifacts inside this lineage directory. Do not edit the live audit skill or parent packet. Do not run `resolveArtifactRoot`.\n+\n+## Research Questions\n+\n+| ID | Question | Status |\n+| --- | --- | --- |\n+| Q1 | What is the current maturity baseline of `design-audit`? | answered |\n+| Q2 | Which improvements are net-new and high leverage rather than duplicate existing references? | answered |\n+| Q3 | Are there routing or parseability defects that can explain imperfect routing scores? | answered |\n+| Q4 | Which operator-facing artifacts would make audits more repeatable? | answered |\n+| Q5 | What benchmark and manual-test additions would make improvements measurable? | answered |\n+| Q6 | Which attractive directions should be rejected as scope creep? | answered |\n+| Q7 | What should be implemented first? | answered |\n+\n+## Iteration Plan\n+\n+1. Inventory the live audit skill and prior 009 research.\n+2. Inspect evidence capture and report template behavior.\n+3. Replay the parseable router against representative audit prompts.\n+4. Review accessibility/performance and quick-fix handoff surfaces.\n+5. Review hardening matrix and production-readiness probes.\n+6. Review AI tell and anti-pattern score calibration.\n+7. Review register-gated transform remediation and cross-mode ownership.\n+8. Check manual testing and benchmark artifact coverage.\n+9. Cull duplicates and scope-creep recommendations.\n+10. Synthesize the ranked recommendation set.\n+\n+## Quality Gates\n+\n+- Cite checked-in files or captured stdout for every load-bearing finding.\n+- Prefer small documentation or fixture additions over new infrastructure.\n+- Preserve audit boundary: audit reports and routes; `sk-code` implements accepted fixes.\n+- Name evidence limitations: packet 014 has no `design-audit` benchmark directory in this checkout; the operator-provided `82/100` score is treated as context, not file evidence.\n+- Keep all writes inside the configured lineage artifact directory.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-001.md\n+# Iteration 001 - Current Audit Inventory\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Establish what `design-audit` already owns so the improvement research does not re-recommend implemented work.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md` describes audit as the cross-cutting QA mode with accessibility, performance, responsive, theming, anti-slop, severity findings, and `/20` score coverage.\n+- The same file requires target/register resolution, evidence labeling, five-dimension scoring, severity-ordered reporting, owner mapping, and no silent implementation during review.\n+- `references/audit_contract.md` already defines P0-P3 severity, 0-4 per-dimension scoring, findings schema, evidence rules, and report order.\n+- `references/corpus_map.md` shows the external audit/critique/polish/harden/optimize/a11y/motion/clarify/pseudo-elements corpus has already been distilled.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The audit mode is mature. Broad expansion would likely duplicate existing references.\n+2. Useful improvements must be operational: routing correctness, evidence capture artifacts, benchmark fixtures, score calibration and handoff ergonomics.\n+3. Prior 009 research recommendations for audit were largely implemented already: report template, AI tell catalog, evidence capture, a11y quick fixes, hardening edge cases and transform remediation.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 1.00.\n+- Open questions reduced: Q1 partly, Q2 partly.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Inspect evidence capture and report template for operator-facing gaps.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+# Iteration 002 - Evidence Capture and Report Ergonomics\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Determine whether audit has enough structure to carry evidence quality through a full report.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `references/evidence_capture.md` resolves targets, defines source/rendered/design-artifact evidence, browser evidence, deterministic scans, screenshot/overlay notes and fallback labels.\n+- `assets/audit_report_template.md` asks for surface, register, evidence available, evidence missing, findings, positive findings, `/20` score, owner mapping, next actions and residual risk.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The evidence model is conceptually complete, but the report template compresses evidence into a small frame. A full audit would benefit from a reusable evidence worksheet that records each target, evidence type, attempted scan, result status and confirmed/inferred/not-assessed label before findings are written.\n+2. The template has owner mapping and next actions, but no backlog-shaped handoff artifact for accepted fixes. A small `audit_backlog_handoff.md` asset would preserve the review/implementation boundary while making `sk-code` handoff less lossy.\n+3. The evidence_capture file already says a dimension with no evidence should be `not assessed`; the score table could make that easier by adding a per-dimension evidence-status column.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.72.\n+- Open questions reduced: Q2 partly, Q4 partly.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Replay the parseable router against representative audit prompts.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+# Iteration 003 - Router Replay and Parseable Defects\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Test whether the parseable `INTENT_SIGNALS` and `RESOURCE_MAP` block routes representative audit prompts to the right resources.\n+\n+## Replay Results\n+\n+| Prompt class | Intents | Resources | Observation |\n+| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n+| Full audit score | `AUDIT_CONTRACT` | `corpus_map`, `audit_contract`, `audit_report_template` | correct core route |\n+| AI-generated surface | `ANTI_PATTERNS_PRODUCTION` | `corpus_map`, `anti_patterns_production`, `ai_fingerprint_tells` | correct focused route |\n+| A11y/performance | `ACCESSIBILITY_PERFORMANCE` | `corpus_map`, `accessibility_performance`, `a11y_quick_fixes` | correct focused route |\n+| Bolder after audit | `AUDIT_CONTRACT`, `TRANSFORM_REMEDIATION` | `corpus_map`, `audit_contract`, `audit_report_template`, `transform_remediation` | correct multi-intent route |\n+| Screenshot-only evidence | `EVIDENCE_CAPTURE` | `corpus_map`, `evidence_capture` | correct focused route |\n+\n+## Defects Found\n+\n+1. The pseudocode loop reads `for keyword, weight in cfg[\"keywords\"]:` even though `keywords` is a list of strings. If executed literally, it is not valid for variable-length keyword strings and ignores the configured `weight`. It should iterate `for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:` and add `cfg[\"weight\"]`.\n+2. Loading levels say `../shared/register.md` is ALWAYS needed, but the parseable `RESOURCE_MAP` and router replay outputs never include the shared register. This matters because full audit scoring and transform remediation depend on the Brand-vs-Product register.\n+3. `_guard_in_skill()` enforces paths under `SKILL_ROOT`, so a naive addition of `../shared/register.md` to `RESOURCE_MAP` would be rejected unless the router gets a deliberate parent-shared exception or a local route to a shared-card proxy.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.58.\n+- Q3 answered; Q5 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Review a11y/performance handoff and implementation-boundary artifacts.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+# Iteration 004 - Accessibility, Performance and Quick-Fix Handoff\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Check whether accessibility/performance findings have actionable but bounded fix references.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `references/accessibility_performance.md` prioritizes accessible names, keyboard, focus/dialogs, semantics, forms/errors, announcements, contrast/states and motion/media.\n+- It gives concrete WCAG contrast, touch target and Core Web Vitals thresholds.\n+- `assets/a11y_quick_fixes.md` gives snippet-level fixes but repeatedly states the audit cites them and `sk-code` applies accepted changes.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. No new a11y basics reference is needed. The current coverage is sufficient and numerically grounded.\n+2. The improvement is handoff shape: a finding should cite the quick-fix section and then a backlog row should carry owner, evidence, target, accepted fix shape and verification command or manual check.\n+3. Do not turn audit into a fixer. The strongest pattern is `audit -> accepted backlog -> sk-code`, not `audit applies snippets`.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.44.\n+- Q4 partly answered; Q6 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Inspect hardening probes and production-readiness run logging.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-005.md\n+# Iteration 005 - Hardening Matrix and Probe Logging\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Assess whether production-readiness probes are repeatable enough for real audit runs.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `references/hardening_edge_cases.md` defines probes for extreme inputs, API/network errors, permissions/rate limits, concurrency, i18n/RTL, text expansion, CJK and emoji.\n+- `references/critique_hardening.md` defines broader cognitive-load, heuristic, persona and hostile-data lenses.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The hardening reference is rich enough. The gap is a run-log artifact that records which probes were run, skipped or inferred for the target.\n+2. The manual playbook accepts SKIP only when no target artifact is supplied, but the skill lacks a reusable per-probe SKIP/FAIL/PASS table for day-to-day audits.\n+3. A combined `audit_evidence_worksheet.md` can include hardening probe rows instead of adding a separate large hardening report template.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.36.\n+- Q2 partly answered; Q4 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Review AI tells and anti-pattern score calibration.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-006.md\n+# Iteration 006 - AI Fingerprint Tells and Score Calibration\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Determine whether model-specific AI tells are actionable enough and whether their impact on the `/20` score is calibrated.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `references/ai_fingerprint_tells.md` lists concrete Codex, Gemini and 2026-general tells with check rules, owner and severity guidance.\n+- `references/anti_patterns_production.md` lists broader anti-slop, theming/token, copy, pseudo-element, View Transition and production-readiness checks.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The AI tell catalog is one of the strongest current assets. Do not replace it with a generic anti-slop essay.\n+2. The remaining gap is score calibration. The catalog says a gallery of three or more tells is at least P1, but the Anti-Patterns 0-4 score could be easier to apply with a compact ladder.\n+3. Recommended addition: a small `anti_patterns_score_ladder` section or asset mapping isolated/systemic tells, user-task impact and register posture to Anti-Patterns score 0-4.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.28.\n+- Q2 partly answered; Q5 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Inspect register-gated transform remediation and cross-mode ownership.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-007.md\n+# Iteration 007 - Register-Gated Transform Remediation\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Check whether `bolder`, `quieter`, `distill` and `redesign` are routed correctly from audit findings to owner modes.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `references/transform_remediation.md` maps the four verbs to finding signals, owner modes and accepted paths.\n+- `shared/register.md` defines Brand vs Product posture and says audit uses the register to weight distinctiveness for Brand and affordance/accessibility/consistency for Product.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. Transform remediation is well scoped. It names direction and owner, and explicitly does not implement the transform.\n+2. The dependency on `shared/register.md` amplifies the router gap from iteration 003. If the register is not loaded, the same observation can be routed to the wrong transform direction.\n+3. The top implementation should fix routing and benchmark this specific class with a prompt like \"Make this interface bolder after the audit identifies why it feels bland.\"\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.21.\n+- Q2 answered; Q3 answered; Q6 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Check manual testing and benchmark coverage.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-008.md\n+# Iteration 008 - Manual Tests and Benchmark Coverage\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Assess how audit improvements can be validated with existing testing artifacts.\n+\n+## Evidence Read\n+\n+- `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md` lists nine scenarios covering score report, transform remediation, evidence capture, report template, a11y/performance, quick fixes, anti-slop, AI tells and hardening edge cases.\n+- `014-routing-benchmark/design-audit/**` had no files in this checkout.\n+- Operator context supplied an audit routing score of `82/100`, but this lineage found no checked-in audit benchmark report to cite.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. Manual scenarios exist and are aligned with the current resource model.\n+2. Missing benchmark fixtures are the clearest measurable gap. Add a design-audit benchmark report and fixtures for the five router replay prompts captured in this lineage.\n+3. Use deterministic router replay for parseable routing and manual playbook scenarios for report-quality behavior. Do not use a single overall score as the only acceptance gate.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.14.\n+- Q5 answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Cull duplicate and scope-creep recommendations.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-009.md\n+# Iteration 009 - Negative Knowledge\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Identify improvements that should not be recommended because they duplicate existing coverage or break the audit boundary.\n+\n+## Ruled Out\n+\n+| Approach | Reason |\n+| --- | --- |\n+| New accessibility basics reference | Already covered by `accessibility_performance.md` and `a11y_quick_fixes.md`. |\n+| Duplicate hardening prose | `critique_hardening.md` and `hardening_edge_cases.md` already cover the narrative and matrix layers. |\n+| Automated overlay/detector claims | Evidence rules forbid claiming browser/overlay/detector evidence unless it actually ran. |\n+| Audit applying fixes | Audit reports and routes; implementation belongs to `sk-code` after user acceptance. |\n+| Bulk import of external corpus | Prior 009 research rejected volume in favor of operational references and cards. |\n+| New audit child skill | Current mode already covers the cross-cutting QA surface; a new child would fragment ownership. |\n+\n+## Finding\n+\n+This mature skill needs precision fixes, benchmark coverage and operator artifacts, not a new taxonomy.\n+\n+## Delta\n+\n+- New information ratio: 0.07.\n+- Q6 answered; Q7 partly answered.\n+\n+## Next\n+\n+Final prioritization and synthesis.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-010.md\n+# Iteration 010 - Prioritized Synthesis\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Converge the lineage into a ranked improvement set.\n+\n+## Final Recommendation Stack\n+\n+1. Fix the router pseudocode keyword loop and make shared-register loading benchmarkable.\n+2. Add `design-audit` routing benchmark fixtures using the five replay prompts from this lineage.\n+3. Add an `audit_evidence_worksheet.md` asset that records target, evidence, attempted probes, confirmed/inferred/not-assessed status, and per-dimension evidence coverage.\n+4. Add an `audit_backlog_handoff.md` asset for accepted findings so audit can hand clean implementation work to `sk-code` without applying fixes.\n+5. Add Anti-Patterns score calibration for AI tells and generic defaults.\n+6. Update the manual playbook to require the new worksheets and benchmark replay evidence when available.\n+\n+## Convergence\n+\n+- All seven research questions answered.\n+- Last three new-info ratios: 0.14 -> 0.07 -> 0.03.\n+- Remaining uncertainty: exact implementation home for parent-shared register loading in the smart router.\n+\n+## Stop Reason\n+\n+Converged at configured maxIterations 10.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":1,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F1\",\"title\":\"Audit mode is mature\",\"summary\":\"Existing audit owns severity, /20 scoring, evidence rules, a11y/performance, critique, anti-patterns, AI tells, hardening and transform routing; broad expansion would duplicate coverage.\"}\n+{\"iteration\":1,\"type\":\"decision\",\"id\":\"D1\",\"summary\":\"Focus improvements on operational leverage, not new taxonomy.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":2,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F2\",\"title\":\"Evidence worksheet gap\",\"summary\":\"The evidence model and report frame exist, but no reusable worksheet carries confirmed/inferred/not-assessed labels through scans, probes, dimensions and findings.\"}\n+{\"iteration\":2,\"type\":\"recommendation\",\"id\":\"R2\",\"summary\":\"Add assets/audit_evidence_worksheet.md or equivalent report adjunct.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":3,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F3\",\"title\":\"Router pseudocode loop defect\",\"summary\":\"SKILL.md iterates `for keyword, weight in cfg[\\\"keywords\\\"]` even though keywords is a string list; the executable form should iterate keywords and add cfg.weight.\"}\n+{\"iteration\":3,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F4\",\"title\":\"Shared register missing from parseable routing\",\"summary\":\"Loading levels require ../shared/register.md, but RESOURCE_MAP and router replay outputs omit it; _guard_in_skill would reject a parent path without a deliberate exception.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":4,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F5\",\"title\":\"Backlog handoff gap\",\"summary\":\"A11y/performance quick fixes are bounded well, but accepted findings need a backlog-shaped handoff to sk-code so audit does not implement fixes itself.\"}\n+{\"iteration\":4,\"type\":\"recommendation\",\"id\":\"R5\",\"summary\":\"Add assets/audit_backlog_handoff.md with owner, evidence, target, accepted fix shape and verification columns.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":5,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F6\",\"title\":\"Hardening run-log gap\",\"summary\":\"The hardening matrix is strong, but audits need a pass/fail/skip/inferred run log for probes to avoid memory-based production-readiness claims.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-006.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":6,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F7\",\"title\":\"Anti-pattern score calibration gap\",\"summary\":\"AI tell rules are concrete, but Anti-Patterns 0-4 scoring needs a compact ladder mapping isolated/systemic tells, task impact and register posture.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-007.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":7,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F8\",\"title\":\"Transform routing depends on register loading\",\"summary\":\"Bolder/quieter/distill/redesign are well scoped, but without the shared register loaded the same observation can route to the wrong owner or direction.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-008.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":8,\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"F9\",\"title\":\"Audit benchmark artifact absent\",\"summary\":\"Manual testing scenarios exist, but no checked-in 014-routing-benchmark/design-audit report was found in this checkout; operator-provided 82/100 remains context rather than file evidence.\"}\n+{\"iteration\":8,\"type\":\"recommendation\",\"id\":\"R9\",\"summary\":\"Add design-audit benchmark fixtures for full-audit, AI tell, a11y, transform and screenshot-evidence prompts.\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/004-audit/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\n+{\"iteration\":9,\"type\":\"negative_knowledge\",\"id\":\"N1\",\"summary\":\"Do not add more a1